{"text": "I will try to tell you as briefly as possible what awaits you in Kingdom: Classic. You will be thrown onto an island in which you must develop your state and hold out for the maximum number of days. You have to call poor people with one coin to your kingdom and give them work, give bows for guards and hunting, hammers for building gardens, towers and walls, and scythes for gold mining. What? Oblique to mine gold? How? It's easy in Kingdom, you give a person a scythe and send him to the garden and he plants gold instead of food, an extremely useful and profitable profession. You will have to defend yourself from the monsters that crawl out of the portals, these portals can be destroyed, but for this you need to create a detachment to attack. To do this, you need to pump the castle for the maximum level and hire a knight, he can lead a detachment of handbrakes and go into battle. Enemies: there are little monsters whose main thing is to steal gold, they do not kill people, but rob and make beggars out of them, a beggar loses his profession and goes into the forest, but he can be returned with one coin. There are also flying monsters that no longer rob but devour people with ends, towers must be installed against them. There are also large monsters that easily destroy fortified walls and spawn small monsters. There are also statues on the island which, if given money, will improve you, a statue of archers will improve archers and a statue of workers will improve walls. Bonus: on the island somewhere in the forest there is a horse that you can change to, it is faster than yours. I hope you enjoyed the review. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
