{"text": "Not a big old school quest, with graphics and controls from the early 90s. It is not entirely clear from the name what it is. Like a dating simulator in which you just need to meet and get to know your hypostases. Pickup teacher so to speak. But this is not so, or rather not quite so. And yet, what could be wrong that two young men meet in the park ?! So, a certain young man named Lou, an Englishman and badly balakin 'in Portuguese, met a girl in a bar, after a couple of bubbles the hunt was strong, he decided to pour out his soul in front of her, the lad liked the guy, and to cement their still green relationship, she gives Lou a date in the park, promising to wait by the pond. Filled with curiosity and driven by the idea and finally to interrupt a series of unsuccessful acquaintances, our elated guy comes the next day to the same place. Upset that no one was there, he decided to explore this rather large park, and this is where this everyday and strange story begins. As I wrote above, this is a simple quest, point and point. We control our boy, examine objects, interact with them. There are no riddles, there are no puzzles with rebuses, everything is simple, you have to think intuitively how to get this or that thing, how to act in a simple situation, read a letter and so on. The picture is just digitized photographs, highly pixelated, which are static, although a little animation and pleasant sounds of nature have been added. Characters too, photos of people frame-by-frame transferred into the game, looks rude, sharp animation of movement not everyone will like. The dialogues, although rather monologues, are interesting. Each subject can be viewed and thought on this score, I personally like these little things. Not protracted, meditative and soothing, except for the sharp movements of Messrs. There is no music, just birds and titmouses are singing, but the breeze rustles the foliage, babble and serenity. In short, I recommend the game. She will show what is \"All ingenious is simple\" and \"What happens when nothing happens\" When triviality can present a strange and even unpleasant surprise with an unexpected twist. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
