{"text": "Wu Lin Zhi is an RPG game with martial arts as the theme, developed by Jianghu Studio using the 3D engine Flexi self-developed by Snail, and published by Snail Company. Wu Lin Zhi adopts an open world mode, players can freely carry out main and side missions, and there are more than 20 martial arts for players to choose which one to join, players can also choose to join the court to fight against martial arts people, the story is quite diverse. The decisions made by the players in the game and the task direction chosen will affect the direction of the ending. There are currently nearly 60 endings in the game for players to explore. The game combat system adopts a turn-based mode. The fighting system is very simple and easy to use. It consists of attack, defense and auxiliary skills, suitable for casual players. Wulin Chi has some of the characteristics of the online game \"Nine Yin Zhenjing\". Players who have played this online game will also like Wulin Chi. The game is valuable and memory invaluable. +The game supports 21:9 display, the picture is not cut or stretched+RPG rich elements in the game+High degree of freedom of the game+The game fighting system is simple, suitable for casual players+The game quality is not bad (with full special effects) +Game soundtrack Not bad + the game comes with Simplified Chinese + the game supports automatic save, manual save and read files at any time-the game cannot modify the resolution, cannot window the game-the game does not support exclusive full-screen games, is not friendly to G-Sync support-the game does not support handles -The game does not support custom buttons-The game cannot adjust the camera rotation speed-The game requires a high computer configuration, and the optimization of multi-core processing is poor-The frequency of game reading is high, which seriously affects the fluency of the game-There is a chance that the game will get stuck during the reading process Machine and crash, especially when the game is opened, it is particularly easy to crash-the game lacks novice tutorials and task guidance-the game does not have steam achievements, does not support cloud archives, and does not have a card system. Wu Lin Zhi is a domestic martial arts game, foreign It is difficult to find RPG games based on martial arts in the game, so Wu Linzhi made me look forward to the game and want to experience this game. Although the game is good overall, the game is really bad in terms of optimization. It takes a long time, often crashes and freezes for no reason, and needs to restart the computer every time, which is very unpleasant during the experience. Although the game supports 21:9 resolution, the game cannot set the resolution by itself. The game will force the full-screen game according to the resolution of the player\u2019s display, and the game cannot be windowed. I have tried the window mode in the game settings, but every time This setting will inevitably cause the system to crash. You must forcibly press the power button to restart the computer, which is a very serious BUG. The full-screen mode in the game is not an exclusive full-screen mode, so players who use G-Sync and multi-screen displays will experience more obvious pauses, and there is no vertical synchronization option in the game. The frequency of reading the game is very high. It takes a certain amount of time to read the disk every time you switch scenes. What is more unacceptable is that you need to read the disk in every lesson. The game progress is quite uneven, so I try to avoid fighting in the big map. Because it is disgusting to wait and read the disk repeatedly. Although the image quality options in the game are abundant, the more basic options mentioned above are absent, which will make players feel that the development team is not careful enough, the camera rotation speed in the game cannot be adjusted, and the keyboard does not support custom keys. The game's combat system is turn-based, and the operation is relatively simple. You only need to be familiar with the combat options of offensive moves, frame moves and air moves. These 3 commands are actually very easy to understand. Players can regard them as rock, paper, scissors, and 3 Commands are all related to each other, but the enemy chooses to defend when attacking, and the enemy can choose to heal. The attacking moves of the game are mainly based on the martial arts moves learned by the player, and the moves can increase their power through skill points. The martial arts moves are mainly divided into 4 categories, namely knives, swords, fists and long handles. I personally recommend choosing a focused practice. If the two minds are divided and invested, it will lead to insufficient damage. Defensive martial arts is relatively simple, there are not too many classifications, basically choose the exercise with high defensive value. Internal strength corresponds to auxiliary martial arts, most of which are based on healing and passive skills. Doing more branches can easily obtain a variety of martial arts cheats. In addition, there are action points, action bars, vigor blood value and internal strength value that need to be paid attention to when fighting. The action points directly determine the upper limit of the character's actions. Each trick has action points that need to be consumed. As long as the action points are still positive, the player can set multiple moves in a round, and the action bar determines the character's action. The speed of the move, the character can move when the action bar is full. The so-called world martial arts is fast and unbreakable, and the priority of moves can always take advantage. The snow value is the player's health value, but when the vitality value is 0, the character will die, and each trick needs to consume internal force. Therefore, when the internal force value is insufficient, some tricks cannot be used. The player needs to properly arrange and calculate the order and all of the moves. The internal force value that needs to be consumed. In fighting, the enemy\u2019s next action intention sometimes appears on the enemy's head. As long as you use the countermeasures to accept the move, but when an enemy with unknown intentions appears, it is recommended to attack or defend as the main objective. Using auxiliary skills will often suffer. Although Wu Lin Zhi is an open world game, the design of the game is a bit boring. There is no clear guidance system for the tasks, and the main and branch lines are too similar. You will encounter a large number of NPCs in the city, and most of them are inconsequential information when you chat with each other. On the big map, you don't have NPCs. The mode of triggering the battle is similar to the classic RPG game. But every time it is triggered, the disk needs to be read, which really needs to be optimized. There are also collection and hunting systems in the game, which are added to the game in the form of a small game similar to Lianliankan. This is a good design for casual players, which can relax the game, but for players with expectations This seems insincere. The game's screen is acceptable, but it is not directly proportional to the configuration requirements. Domestic 3D games have a common problem, that is, the optimization is poor, and there is no exclusive driver optimization. It can only be optimized by the developer itself. Developers are allowed to spend their budgets on optimization. Players experience poor and manufacturers can\u2019t make money. Then the next step is worse. It is a vicious circle. Developers need to find a balance so that manufacturers can make money. Players will not be optimized. Problem and bad review of the game. As for the music, it's quite satisfactory. It didn't shine, but there was no obvious problem. The personal decision about the positioning of the game is not a large-scale game, it can only be regarded as a skit. If it is a casual game, I don\u2019t think it is true, because many of the systems in the game apply the gameplay of other games or long-term game methods. There is no place for innovation. If you want to operate it, you can only rely on the keyboard to move the character. It is obviously a turn-based game that can definitely be optimized to complete all operations with a mouse alone, but the manufacturer does not have that design, and the game does not support the handle, and the keyboard is hard for players. You can't play happily. In the current version, the personal recommendation is 5/10. If the optimization and flash card machine problems can be solved, the personal recommendation is 7/10. -Optimize the game configuration requirements, solve the problem of stuck machine and flashback-Optimize the frequency and speed of reading disks-Add options for adjusting resolution, vertical synchronization, windowing and exclusive full screen-Add options for adjusting lens movement speed-Add handle support -Add custom buttons-Optimize the guidance system for game tasks-Add steam cloud save, steam achievements and steam card system ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
