{"text": "When I heard about the release of this game, I had mixed feelings. Life is Strange made me fall in love with its originality, interesting plot and it seemed to me that nothing could be done better, as it usually happens. I've never been so wrong. Every moment creeps through to the very creeps, the musical accompaniment immerses you in the atmosphere of events with your head, helping to subtly feel all the emotions. During the game, you mentally replay the scenes from the first part and you stop believing that this is all - the beginning of the story of Life is Strange. And I want to note that its beginning hooked me much more than the story with the protagonist in the person of Max, who got confused in time and her abilities. We get to know the characters of the first part from the other side. We are experiencing the problems of the main character, from childhood trauma to adolescent maximalism. And a long-awaited acquaintance with the most important mystery of Life is Strange - everyone's beloved Rachel Amber. This was so lacking! But I would not have felt this \"boom\" of emotions without playing the first part. Perfectly. And it hurts too much. 9/10 - the last scene finishes it off. There weren't enough handkerchiefs to stop the ocean of tears. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
