{"text": "Euro Truck Simulator 2 is an almost perfect trucker simulator. You start the game as an ordinary \"driver\" without your own truck and are engaged in transportation on various trucks of employers, naturally getting much less money than if you were engaged in transportation on your personal truck. Over time, you accumulate funds and buy your first truck; by the way, you can take out a bank loan for this business. The game provides a pretty decent tuning system: body, engine, chassis, transmission, cab, headlights, mirrors, handles, tires and even airbrushing (a separate set with the Scandinavian gods can be bought as DLC), it's nice that the tuning of the iron is not just for show \"it really affects the behavior of your truck on the road. Then you are engaged in the transportation of various goods, save up funds, and when you accumulate a tangible amount, the question arises: \"Where can I spend all this stuff?\" - and still have something to spend. ETS 2 turns at a different angle and you turn from a driver into a manager: buying garages, expanding them, hiring drivers, buying them trucks - all these are now your direct responsibilities, but if all this management is alien to you, you can just hammer a bolt on this business and to continue as if nothing had happened to be engaged only in transportation. The sounds in the game are decent, you will also be pleased with the roar of the engine from the pressurized cabin. You can listen to your Mueyka in the game by specifying the directory to the folder, or listen to the built-in radio with all popular stations from pop to metal, by the way, if your favorite radio station is missing, you can drive it manually. The graphics are probably the only thing you can find fault with, but you don't want to do this, and in the recent huge patch it was pretty decently tweaked. ETS 2 certainly deserves familiarization, if only for the fact that it really teaches you to drive correctly, huge fines for driving on red, driving into the oncoming lane, speeding, driving with the headlights off at night, still motivate you to drive correctly, and not only that. Over time, these fines will seem like pennies, but getting into accidents, and if you do not follow the rules here, you will definitely get into them, decent money is lost for damaged cargo and repairing your truck. Overall, my rating for the game is 9.5 / 10. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
