{"text": "I'll write a GTA Online review when I load ... ... ... ... ... ... (after 10 minutes) ... Ok, I'm here. So, about GTA 5: Simulator of downloads and gatherings in the lobby. 1) Do you want to play online - download 10 minutes 2) Create a lobby for robbery - download 2 minutes 3) Wait for people to connect - from 10 to 60 minutes you are again on the boot screen reading about what an oxyenne machine Vapid Ellie is. After all the suffering, you suddenly find a team, go through the task with it, look at how much money you received and download again. You wait 5 minutes. 10 minutes. 15 minutes. 40 minutes, you memorize everything that is written on the loading screen. Congratulations, you are on endless loading, Alt F4. You send everything to hell and go play the race. After a series of short downloads, you finally finish the race and the game decides not to leave the voting menu. The only thing that warms my heart is that now 10 more people are stuck with you. You swear in the chat, and again Alt F4. You go to a robbery to another person. You also sit in the lobby and load, but after loading you find that your HUD has not loaded and you are stuck in the limb due to the fact that someone else has started an endless loading. You realize that you can't even bring up the pause menu, you can only run, jump and swear in the chat. The hand is already reaching for Alt F4, but you remember that you can get out of the limb with the help of friends by connecting to their session. You open Social Club, but all your friends are offline, because it's already deep in China. Alt F4. And so the game is cool! Recommend! ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
