{"text": "4:00 p.m .: this is the time it took me to re-loop one of my favorite games that I bought in a flea market 15 years ago Suffice to say that, once again on Steam, I did a very compulsive purchase as soon as the Remastered of my baby in the shop. 30 Euros in the mouth plus \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, I immerse myself in this beautiful story that is MAFIA. A living story more than an open world game like MAFIA II and III were. Through around 15 chapters you relive the important moments in the life of Thomas Angello, a modest taxi driver who became a member of a mafia family. I said no more, all the interest of this game lies in its scenario, as well as in the quality of its decoration. It is therefore essential not to look for the spoils of the game, nor to watch too much live, it would totally spoil the experience. The effect of a bullet through poor Tommy's head. Otherwise, it's a very linear game. No extreme combat, no awesome physics effect, in short nothing that would set the game apart from any other in this price range. Just be content to live the adventure of your character. However, you are entitled to great sensations of virtual driving, very beautiful vehicles, beautiful shootouts with the sulphate, a very nice soundtrack. Well, ultimately it's not gross. Like the very first game in its time finally ... Now let's talk about the bad points, because life is too short not to spend it criticizing the World: The game is much too simple, Even in \"Classic\" mode (which resumes the difficulty of the original game) which is deemed \"difficult\" by the studio. In principle this is true, except that everything is spoiled by the health bar, the last 20% of which recharges after 5 seconds. If we are not too light on the helmet in terms of strategy, we will never die in this game. Especially since you have throughout missions, medikits and ammunition boxes, the use of which is strictly reserved for Tommy. It would be sacrilegious for an enemy to use these sacred reserves. Only the police become a small challenge in itself, since they are very reactive in the face of your incivility, especially on the highway code. However still, with their old sedans, you quickly access in the game more powerful cars for the seeded. To conclude, I have to recommend this game. Even if I am a little over my hunger in terms of challenge. For fans like me of the very first MAFIA, it is a duty to have the so-called \"Definitive\" version. Now I will calmly resume the game to finish all that remains, the magazines and cars to recover. Once the last achievement is unlocked, I will say my final farewells to my old friend Tommy. After all he is from the Family;) ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
