{"text": "The first chapter of Reversion is a very short adventure game. It can be completed in less than an hour, but it's fun to play, especially for someone who likes to play adventure games. The somewhat hackneyed theme with an amnesic hero isn't very original, but let's say it works. The puzzles are sensible, not overcomplicated, so the game can be completed without using guides. There is also no need to hunt for some hidden single pixel, although not all items are applicable in the game - some only serve to build the atmosphere and add some humor. I found the interface tiring, requiring double clicking to bring up the menu. This can be solved much simpler - it would be enough to hold the button or even right-click. Not a big complaint, but it did ruin the game a bit. The graphics are pleasing to the eye - readable, cartoonish, a bit caricatured. The game is full of humor, also in terms of achievements. Here I have another objection - I don't like the achievements for \"another completion of the game\", especially if this additional pass does not differ from the first one. There are no different paths here, you just have to click through the adventure again. The game is free, so for the price - it's definitely worth a try. TL; DR Nice and nice adventure game, easy and humorous. Very short but free. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
