{"text": "When PlayStation Home shut down, I was devastated. The Casino space on there was one of the coolest spots to hang out, as well as the complimentary hotel room personal space. I'm very grateful that Digital Leisure picked up the pieces and made their own virtual social world. In fact, the user interface is a lot like how PS Home was, as far as opening a menu to dance or pose. And man, those facial expressions when your character is dancing is hilarious. I honestly wish that more players would be online to play with. Four Kings isn't cross compatible with PS4, which apparently is where more players of this game are on. As a Steam player, I would go to the Nightclub area and it would be dead empty. And I would be lucky to find another player to play Bowling with me. Some of the music in this game is repetitive and annoying, so I just mute the game music and play some of my own tracks in the background, like from YouTube or something. The Nightclub tracks aren't bad though! This game is a lot of fun with the variety of casino games to play! As this is a successor to PlayStation Home, I do have to recommend this game to everybody. I just would like to see more content, such as personal spaces (and customization options for them?), as well as more outfits and locomotions. Again, if more Steam players played on here, the better! -- EDIT (09/27/2018): This IS Free-to-Play, however, I don't think the microtransactions to RENT a Dance Party, or a silly walk is right. Especially if the game glitches, that's just a waste of money for the user. I don't like that. But again, I support a successor of PlayStation Home and only wish for better improvements in the future! ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
