{"text": "Unfortunately, there is no neutral feedback on the incentive, so I'll write, perhaps, a positive one. Because the overall game for 2013 is not bad. To a greater extent, here, of course, the style of the game, mixing cyberpunk and fantasy, is a very successful technique. The interaction of magic with technology makes the game exciting, the world where people and \"metal people\" get along seems full and interesting. Unfortunately, the game's engine is bad, sometimes FPS sags during a battle, although it would seem that the game's requirements are insignificant, the combat itself is also not very successful, sometimes annoying, but in general there are interesting moments, like summoning a spirit from a shaman or transitions to matrix, but still by the 5th hour of the game it becomes clear that combat is very primitive. With Music, too, in principle, everything is expected 2-3 compositions, but they do not get boring and correspond to the declared style to who is also waiting for Hans Zimmer in such a game. Perhaps the most valuable thing that the developers managed to achieve is an interesting plot, personally I was interested in playing only thanks to him, in order to find out the outcome, not to say that he is some kind of abstruse, but interesting, although to my deepest regret he systematically slides towards the end of the game ... In fact, summing up, we can say that playing at 6/10 is not bad, but also nothing special except for the setting. If you want to kill a couple of evenings in a game where turn-based combat and the distant future are in the yard, then this game is quite suitable, since it does not have an overpriced price tag. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
