{"text": "Before i bought the game, I have received a good feedback on this game. It was on sale, so i had to buy it, and lemme tell you, i have never been so happy before about buying a game for 47 euros. It might be a bit salty for my wallet, but it was worth it. First things first, Customization - I took me an hour to customize my character. The variety of hair styles, appearance, emotions, voice is just huge. For example if you try to make yourself, it will take some time to decide between which lip shape to choose. Second, Landscapes - I just love, LOVE games with some beautiful sceneries. When i play open world games like this i really love to take alot of screenshots, so this is just perfect for me. Third, Story - Story is like one of the important things for me, when i pick up a new game. Since i have played this only for an hour, i can't really tell anything about it yet. So far i have seen some characters, and some action going on at the beginning of the game. Forth, Multiplayer - As much as i have seen other streamers play this game, the monster fights are HARD, so its SUPER handy if you have a friend to play this game with, because its much easier like that. So this is a really good game to pick up, if you are looking for a game to play with your friends as well. Overal - The game is beautiful and full of adventure. The game might have costed 47 euros, but i am so damn positive, that i won't regret the decision of buying it. P.S. Since the game is about fighting monsters, this will be one damn good game to grind, with endless monster fights. Gotta get my game face on ( \u00cd\u00a1\u00e2\u2014\u2030 \u00cd\u0153\u00ca\u2013 \u00cd\u00a1\u00e2\u2014\u2030) ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
{"text": "Trine is an excellent 2D platform game, beautiful scenarios (which were much better when the game received the update that made it Enchanted Edition). I recommend zeroing the game in co-op with friends. Anyone who played Trine before it became Enchanted Edition must also zero in again, with the new graphics. My favorite character is the magician, I can't get enough of creating boards, boxes and pyramids with the crown. You can buy it and you won't regret it. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
{"text": "While playing ATS, you inevitably start comparing it with ETS2, in order to somehow note for yourself the progress achieved in a relatively new product from SCS Software. What can ATS offer us? After several hours of playing, the answer immediately suggests itself: except for a change of location and a little tighter graphics, nothing new. Despite the fact that the map of those several states can really be called rich and well-developed, this is still not enough. I don't know why, but apart from the three Southern States on the border with Mexico, there are no more territories for exploration in the game, while in the same ETS2 a map of most of continental Europe is implemented, along with Great Britain and the Scandinavian Peninsula. In addition, the predominantly desert landscapes outside the window soon begin to get bored, and this is with all the climatic diversity of North America. As for the technology, the situation here is much more tragic, we were given a choice of 2 companies with 4 tractors, for which there are several modifications of the same type of body and chassis, and there are practically no opportunities for tuning. It can be seen that this game has a reserve for the long-term implementation of new functionality, most likely in the form of paid DLCs that are already available for it, but the game is not worth its money, specifically at the moment. As a result, after the game, there is a persistent feeling that you have been bred somewhere for money, but after you have played several hundred hours in ETS2 on several accounts at once, you want something new, and perhaps ATS will someday be yourself will justify. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
{"text": "This game is simply gorgeous. The graphics and sounds are rich and immersive. Gameplay is true to the franchise and if you like previous Tomb Rider titles you can't go wrong on this one. There's everything: strange places to explore, tombs and corpses, lurking enemies and dangerous animals, just like the good old times. this time a very light RPG-like skill point system lets you choose and refine your tomb-riding abilities. No swimming or riding vehicles in this one, but you get a bow which is very fun to use. Lara has become more human and the environment more real and unforgiving. The story won't win an Oscar soon but is not bad either. I find this last step in the franchise evolution a solid one, and even deserving a sequel. Tomb Rider is playable in a wide range of systems due to its spec flexibility. MP is a weakness but not as they want you to believe. A bit laggy, a bit confusing and lacking players, the maps are interesting and the weapons accept some grade of customization. Download all single player content (minus cheats) and don't get the rest until you have actually tried MP. Most is aesthetic, and the Hitman guns unecessary. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
