{"text": "Albeit a short, but very interesting game. Little Nightmares, this game is about ... oh ... What about? About a little girl who is trying to escape from some unknown place and from some unknown person? This is an approximate understanding of the game you will have at first. Here they do not lead by the handle, do not poke their noses, they tell little about the plot, and therefore you have to pay more attention to details in order to understand something. As you progress through the game, it becomes more and more gloomy, and some aspects are opened from a new side, thereby creating even more questions. After passing, an aftertaste of obscurity remains. They did not give the desired answers to your questions, which gives you food for thought, the construction of theories and a reason to google the plot of the game, since there are some comics on the game and they at least explain something. In general, the game turned out to be good, for an evening or two, in some places you can get stuck for a few minutes, you have to use your brains. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
