{"text": "Well now. This game is going to be controversial. I like it but a lot of people won't. This is a game that defies expectations. It clearly owes more than a little to David Lynch (not just Twin Peaks). If anything, it's like an interactive film.  Sure, a lot of people will say 'This is not a game!' or hurl around walking simulator. But the devs always made that pretty clear. If that doesn't appeal to you - simply stay away, there's a lot of other games out there. The game is absolutely beautiful visually and the music and audio is great. There is not a single spoken word in the game which strengthens it as far as I'm concerned but may be jarring for others. The writing is outstanding, one of the best I've seen in a short game. It really does a good job (better than most) in putting you in the shoes of the character you play. Virgina is short and quite frankly somewhat railroady. If you're okay with that, great. Otherwise stay away. In summary, if you like games where it's all story and the game revolves around the experience and narrative, not the mechanics this is a great one. If that's not your thing - just say away. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
