{"text": "-The game: In Rainbow Six Siege, the player cannot behave in the same way as he would in an FPS like Call of Duty, which has a faster pace, vehicles and the option to revive after being shot down. What happens here is the other way around: each step must be well thought out, and this helps to build an atmosphere of adrenaline and tension that is one of the great highlights of the game. The movements of the characters, the scenarios very well constructed and the communication between players of a team result in an interesting and realistic tactical FPS experience. In general, the matches are very challenging and effective in giving gamers the feeling that special forces soldiers must feel in each operation. - Operators: With each game, you earn reputation points in the game. With this, it is possible to unlock new \"operators\", which are different types of agents for each special organization depicted in the shooting game (SWAT, GIGN, SAS, Spetsnaz and GSG9 among others according to the DLC). Each has different characteristics of equipment, weapons and movements. When unlocking agents, the player can also customize their properties. There are several add-ons for weapons, both functionalities and appearance, which give each gamer a varied list of agents at his disposal so that he can choose which is the most appropriate for each game situation. This is another very positive point of the Rainbow Six Siege experience for its players. The gameplay can change a lot according to each operator used. There is a variation of objective in each round - which makes the game more unpredictable and demands that each player specialize in \"doing everything\". Each round, your team \"attacks\" or \"defends\". Those who defend protect a device or a hostage, while those who attack must recover the items. Defenders have time to prepare, place barricades, barbed wires and other resources to prevent the invasion of enemies, who try to find their targets with drones. Summary: Graphics: 9 Gameplay: 10 Fun: 8 (it's a competitive game, you have to take it seriously) Sound: 10 Pros: Very realistic gameplay; Stimulates cooperation between players; Fully in Portuguese; Variety of agents, weapons and equipment; Very well-built scenarios Cons: Absence of history mode; Difficulty may be too high, but it improves depending on your skill; Few game modes; Some kids, but not much; ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
