{"text": "One of the most iconing point&click adventure games from lucas arts. Like with previous remasters from Double fine, you are given a choice to seamlessly switch between original visuals and remastered ones. Similarly you can either switch between original midi sound score and remastered sampled one.  Personally i find of remastered sound with classic visuals and director comentary the most satisfying combination of the available options.   A no brainer purchase for adventure newcomers and veterans  alike.  PROS:  Oldimers will appreciate updated sound and smooth gamplay without of hassle of messing around with either dosbox or scummvm. New players will appreciate timeless cartoonish style, hillarious dialogue and insane puzzles in style of early LA production  CONS:  Remastered visuals are somewhat lacking in detail as if original graphics had been just retraced in vector painting app, giving the the visuals feel of a browser flash game.  Some puzzles may be a bit more challenging than what players are used to in current games.  A large part of the puzzle design revolves around indirect interaction beween the 3 main protagonists via something akin to message in the bottle mechanic. While ingenious in concept, it can sometimes lead to being stuck for extended periods of time as the necessary interaction is not easy to guess. eaxmple: bernard(present) needs to stick hamster in into icebox so it freezes, so laverne(future) can thaw it and use hamster in solving the puzzle in future ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
