npc Finally, I won\u2019t be slapped every time). If you like to relax, you can try the original version first. \u25cfAdjust the running speed and global speed with the help of modifiers. The combat speed of the original version of the game is almost deadly slow. In the middle and late stages, one action is put for a long time, and people can't stand it; when the characters are running, they are the same as slow motion. Modifying the game speed through shortcut keys can save a lot of time, make the protagonist run more smoothly and naturally with the help of light work, and reduce the fatigue caused by the battle time. (After adding super jumps and continuous jumps, it really feels like flying over the walls, coming and going freely, now I want to jump when I see the house...) \u25cfReset the perception, martial arts and other attributes of the protagonist and the npc through the modifier, and modify it The real-time adjustment of the player can modify the play ideas of the protagonist and teammates at any time (note that it should not be over-enhanced and disrupt the balance of the game) to fully experience the game content. \u25cfModify the difficulty in real time through the modifier, so there is no need to manually change the archive parameters to modify the difficulty. \u25cfThe above modifiers are all included in \"Xiaoxing Modifier\", it also contains other powerful functions, such as adding any teammates, npc, etc., adjust it according to your own preferences. (If it weren't for other functions such as the reset and acceleration of the modifier, it would be really tiring to play. The screen is full of shit; the vertical painting and the dubbing are good. The battles are always one after another and cannot be saved. If you lose, you have to start from the beginning; You can\u2019t quit during the battle, you can only use Alt+F4; the skill shortcut key slot is less, and it can only be set in the battle; the task positioning is not accurate, and the prompt is often not in place. Many operations are anti-human. \u25cfIt is said in other reviews. Very detailed, there are too many details. In many cases, you can only choose one of two to be good people and good things. Many tasks have more than 3 solutions. I don't know at all without looking at the strategy. If a trivial task is studied deeply, it may be It leads to a series of leave, of course, you can also choose to quickly understand the matter from the beginning; many tasks need to go to different places at different times to trigger or unlock hidden content. Sometimes you don\u2019t know if you don\u2019t look at the strategy. There are too many hidden factors, everywhere. Details and foreshadowing. \u25cfThe early and mid-term missions did too many branches and too detailed, and the later missions obviously felt rushed. \u25cfThe original and pirated version of \"The Witcher 3\" played for hundreds of hours, and the design of the \"Helo\" mission was compared \"The Witcher 3\", I personally think that the former is better than the latter in many places, and the choice of many tasks in the latter will not bring too many changes. The task design of the former is really very diverse, full of details, and very suitable for the Chinese The taste of \"Holo\" is very grounded. But the plot expressiveness of \"Holo\" is much worse than that of \"The Witcher 3\". The latter brings players much deeper feelings than the former. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
