{"text": "I will not copy the article from Wikipedia and do not want to come up with anything long. I'll just write this: CS: GO is a complex and slightly convoluted esports game that will hardly ever die. The community of this game will be rather difficult to describe in 2 words, but it can be divided into 2 camps: Russian dybily English-speaking community English-speaking Russians There are 2 types of ranks in the game: private (the one that rises due to the experience that is given after each game on official servers) and \"basic\" (obtained by playing matchmaking or competitive mode in Russian) Physics is an integral and rather difficult part of the game. Here you can shoot at 1 enemy with AK47, and hit the one that was behind. It's simple: unlike CSS, CS: GO has more \"realistic\" (according to Volvo) physics. It is more difficult to bhop here, bullets fly up / sideways, sometimes even randomly. And all this still somehow contrives to complicate. An example of this will be the recent update * Tec-9, a rather imbibed pistol, which is now worse than the Five-seven (for me). Previously, it was a semi-automatic with a large magazine and high accuracy, but now it is game with 18 rounds in the magazine and wild spread at long distances. Some people who have already played a decent number of hours in the game and have a high rank (L.E.-G.E.) * This game gets bored because gives nothing and it is \"just a waste of time\". NO! I'll tell you. In the final game, you can learn a lot, especially if you start playing at the age of 13-14. Here: -Your farts are getting hot -You are learning a team game (at least by the example of cybersportsmen) -You can learn how to create tactics (like in chess: D) -You can raise money from nothing -Find new friends -Learn a little English -Just learn more about people -To lose a lot of money for cases -Become a Youtuber in cops Well, or in the end, get a party of 5 people and get crazy. Bottom line: Siesgou is something strange, a little clumsy and unpredictable creature. This is \"not fish or meat\", this is something unnatural, synthetic, so to speak, soy meat * ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
