{"text": "Grab your gun and shoot, that's how things work out. Walker does not find another solution, he is a soldier and believes that his objective is to help but at any cost. It is something that the game teaches us in the first room, but events teach us something else, not everything is what it seems. Spec Ops sin for a loop, a scene from the story and then shoot. This is repeated throughout the entire game. Hordes of enemies are coming and your mission is to kill them. I miss a little more dynamism, something that breaks with that routine. The good thing is that it is not a generic shooter, its story is far from all that. Its well-kept settings is something that impacts. You can find very hard images, which makes us see what a soldier can find in wars. Its graphics are not the best but to be 2012 not too bad. Your two companions are alive, they have their own dilemmas and everything that is happening affects them. Even enemies have their conversations that make you think. Well, I absolutely recommend it. It can have its bad things and maybe the first episodes are not so shocking, but the game is improving and the end is the best. You will not find a typical story of the war genre and I think he knows how to handle what a soldier can feel and how things affect him. It lasts about 6 hours like this, it will not make you heavy at any time. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
