{"text": "I cooled down a moment after going through the supplement and I will share my impressions as announced. I would like to mention that it will not be an objective assessment, because I am a huge fan of the whole universe and I waited a long time for this expansion. Let's also take a correction to my infinite love for Yennefer <3 But let's move on to the modification itself. As you may know, this is a fan mod (from fans to fans). The main theme is the wedding of our (my) beloved couple: Yennefer and Geralt. However, don't be fooled! During the game, we will play the role of various heroes (Ciri, Eskel, Letho) and get to know new stories or brighten up previously known ones (there are many flashbacks). However, despite the many tasks to be performed, we will spend wonderful moments at the wedding of the young couple. The very implementation of the add-on is a real masterpiece. The world has been reproduced perfectly, and the creation of characters and dialogues is a miracle. They reflect 100% the character of the heroes we know from books or games. Everything has been adjusted to the last button and Redzi would not be ashamed of it! The story presented in the modification is extraordinary and very well thought out. Everything is connected together in an original way, and the additional tasks to be performed only emphasize the uniqueness of this adventure. They bring us even closer to the heroes of the saga, show new events and a new perspective. Also worthy of recognition is the fact of many endings (3 to be exact). I had a banana from ear to ear all over my face! Seeing the references to the saga and the games, I literally jumped for joy (really!) And laughed at the screen. My little heart rejoiced like never before. It was a real dream come true and it means more to me than you can imagine. And at the end of tears my eyes. Huge drops obscuring the screen. \"Something is ending ..\". A certain stage is definitely over. However, I want to think that \"something begins\". I don't know what it will be yet. I feel a great void knowing that this is the end of the adventures of my beloved White Wolf, Yennefer, Ciri and their companions. However, I couldn't imagine a better ending to this story. Beautiful. Touching. Moving. And at the same time joyful. The supplement is brilliant. The creators put their whole heart into the modification, thanks to which they created a unique and unique story. A story worth experiencing for yourself. But be warned, nothing will ever be the same again. I might take it too personally, but that's my charm <3 I calmed down a little after finishing this mod and as I said, I will share my opinion about it. I also want to say that it won't be objective, because I'm a huge fan of the Witcher universum and I've been waiting for so long for this dlc. Don't forget about my endless love for Yennefer <3 But let's focus on the modification now. As you may know, this is a fan expansion (from fans to fans). The main story is Yennefer and Geralt's wedding: our (my) lovely couple. But don't misunderstand that! During the gamplay we'll play as different characters (Ciri, Eskel, Letho) and experience new stories or get to know ones, that we already know (there are a lot of flashbacks). Despite a lot of tasks to do, we'll spend a lovely time at newlyweds' wedding. The creation of the mod is masterpiece. The world is mapped perfectly and the creation of the characters and dialogues is wonderful! They mapped the characters we know from books or games in 100%! CDPRed wouldn't be ashamed! The story's showed in the mod is unique and very thoughtful. Everything is connected in an original way and extra tasks just emphasize the specialness of this adventure. They bring us closer to the characters that we know from the books and games, they show new events and perspective. Let's also appreciate multiple endings (3 to be extact). All the time I was smiling from ear to ear! Seeing the references to books or games make me literally jumping up and down with excitement (really!) And I was laughing to the screen. My heart was over the moon like never before. My dream came true and it means for me more, than you can expect. And at the end tears in my eyes. Big drops covering my screen. \"Something ends ...\". For sure a certain stage ends. But I want to think, that \"something begins\". I don't know what it is yet. I feel empty knowing, that this is the end of my favorite White Wolf, Yennefer, Ciri and their friends' adventures. But I couldn't imagine better ending of this story. Beautiful. Moving. Touching. And delighting at the same time. The modification is brilliant. Authors put their hearts and soul in this dlc, that's why they've created unique and touching story. The story worth experiencing on your own. But I warn you, nothing will be the same. Maybe I'm too emotional, but that's my charm <3 ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
