{"text": "In Another Brick in the Mall you are the owner of your own mall. You start with a big plot of land and money, so that you can start building a small supermarket. After a while you can expand if you research new technologies like alcohol, restaurants, movies etc. Additionally you have to take care of the traffic - you need to build roads, parking spots (of course for customers, but also for your employees and suppliers). Later you can unlock more accesses to your roads and busses, with that you get a lot more customers - and money, of course. Another big part is the personal management. You need to hire cashiers, storemans, builders and so on. After you hired them, you need to give your employees a shift, so that they know when and how long they should work. Every of your stores has its own employees, so you need to hire cashiers and storemans for every single store. That can be boring with time but it's important for a well-functioning store. Later you can build self-checkouts, but not every customer wants to use them, so you need \"human\" cashiers as well. All in all AbitM is a nice and relaxing game. It's nice to see how customers buy your products and how you make money. The personal management can be boring with time, as well as the placing of streets and parking spots. In many areas it reminds of Prison Architect, if you liked it, ABitM is definitely something for you! + Nice concept + Many different stores + A lot to research - Often annoying personal management - Too much money in the late game *It is a lot of fun to build you own mall and to manage it *Nothing special - but okay for a game like this *No music - only standard sounds like cars *No bugs, good performance *An acceptable amount of content for this price *Many updates, dev answers in forum, mod support *Easy to learn ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": true}
{"text": "This game hides what you really want to express in the details. There is only one core setting of the game, that is, the number of points in the test and the university you go to have nothing to do with future achievements. The entire game content is developed around this point of view. What our parents, teachers, and teaching assistance organizations often promote is that only by taking high scores and attending prestigious schools can we have a good future and hope. The setting of this game directly negates this. 0 points can be an Olympic champion, 400 points or so can be the world's richest man. And even if the IQ is high, if you don\u2019t study the subjects related to the college entrance examination, you will get a very low test, and you can only go to a technical school if you can\u2019t even go to university. It is ability, not achievement, that determines the future. This gave the so-called Chinese-style education a resounding slap. Although this setting is in line with the facts, it is impossible for most parents to accept it, and it is not in line with our main theme. It's not that studying hard is useless. Study hard to become a white-collar worker. However, white-collar workers are the most boring profession in this game. If you want to really achieve great achievements, such as becoming an Olympic champion, the world's richest man, a big star, an internet celebrity, a ninja master, etc., you must never follow the so-called \"good student\" route, especially the plan of your parents. What we have to do is to act against the yin. On the surface, I am studying every day to prevent game over. In private, I am constantly exposed to content that has nothing to do with the college entrance examination and do what I want to do. And stick to it. What is the use of learning value investment for the college entrance examination? What is the use of learning video production for the college entrance examination? What is the use of learning the way of ninja for the college entrance examination? What is the use of learning modeling training for the college entrance examination? But these are exactly what we need when making plans for our lives. On the contrary, it is the Comprehensive Liberal Arts Comprehensive, Huanggang X Volume, these are the most useless. If life is a marathon, then these things are disposable items that are thrown away when they are used up. Two years later, who will remember them. In the game, if we learn the corresponding ability, then it doesn't matter how many points are tested. As for what school to enter, that is the moment when the admission notice pops up. As for the future and destiny, it has nothing to do with your school. Do not do most. I think this is the inspiration this game brought to me. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
