{"text": "S.T.A.L.K.E.R. - The Call of Pripyat is the last part of the saga so far, which ends our adventure with the world of \"Zona\" in a commendable way. Basically, this part is for me what \"Shadow of Chernobyl\" was supposed to be, i.e. large locations that allow you to play the way we like. Expressive characters, which are no longer a cluster of pixels without character, the side quests are finally not random as in the previous parts, but are varied, usually having an interesting background - the exception here is the main storyline with boring missions and a poor storyline, the modification system has been slightly rebuilt so so that at the beginning the character would not be OP and the mission to return to the \"underground\";) The core of the game remained the same, the authors almost came to know their own \"engine\" in 100%, thanks to which the game does not crash, every now and then, but further occasional bellows occur. The shooting itself is not as stiff as before, but the A.I. It deserves a downside for me, because as far as I was thinking about my next move, here I was almost sure of winning in each match. At the same time, the atmosphere ricochets, because we don't feel so hated anymore - which is a pity. If you've played the previous games, like post-apo or open-world FPS, you'll be very happy with this game, I recommend it. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
