{"text": "The story told in the game is amazing, and its main highlight is the presentation. With a fairly simple general concept of the plot, the developers managed to make a very lively story, over and over again causing a lot of emotions in the player. All this is conveyed through various details, the relationship of the characters, precisely chosen remarks and unexpected situations. The action of the game takes place in a large open world, one cannot call it empty. I would like to look into every corner. A lot of side quests are offered, of course most of them are template, but there are also quite interesting ones, in any case, the game gives out great rewards for completing quest chains. The combat system is completely new, not turn-based, there is a tactical mode with an active pause, the heroes have a lot of weapons in their arsenal, and taking into account the diversity of the local fauna, the battles turned out to be quite boring. The quartet of the main characters came out just fine. All of them are bright and charismatic personalities, whom you respect more and more as you progress. We play as the prince and heir to the prince, his personal bodyguard, future advisor and childhood friend of the prince. And if at the beginning of the game they look like idiots, then by the end of the game you admire their devoted friendship and the unshakable will of their comrades. The graphics in the game are gorgeous, it can be safely called nextgen, even at low settings the game is capable of producing a juicy picture, and at maximum graphics it approaches the quality of CGI content. The sound did not disappoint either, the music pleases the ears and the atmosphere is also in order. Localization, it is excellent, FF XV is completely translated into Russian and not anyhow. The voices of the heroes are selected as accurately as possible, you feel a good acting game, at some point the game becomes so familiar and you already forget that the game was made in the land of the rising sun. + Incredibly atmospheric and touching story. + \"Live\" characters. + Full localization into Russian. + A boring combat system. + The presence of a well-thought-out endgame. + The car and the ability to tune it in every way. + Insanely beautiful world of the game. + Fishing is very smart and entertaining. + Dishes from Ignis. + The atmosphere of adventure. + Subject add-ons included. - Monotonous side quests. - Rare but well-aimed departures. - High system requirements. - Part of the plot is taken out of the game (Film + Anime series), to please the western player. - The mathematics of the combat system turned out to be very simple, unusual for the series. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
{"text": "In practice, the PC version of Dead Effect 2 is no different from the mob version. devices. After the new update, the situation in the game has improved, the optimization came out good. I did not notice any FPS drawdowns. I had no other problems. The game also has enough advantages. Let's start with the best part - the graphics are excellent. No, seriously, for a game on the Unity engine, it is very beautiful. The second plus is the RPG elements, during the passage of missions (story and additional) you can get various bonuses in the form of a helmet, body armor, etc. There is also a pumping of weapons and skills (include the skills of the first game: time dilation). There are also a lot of weapons, both from the first part and new ones. There is no need to talk about enemies here. The developers knowingly added opponents in the face of which are not only zombies, but also people. AI is good, there are no complaints about it. About the game, I can say that the developers have tried their best, you can\u2019t say anything. But this optimization is frustrating. I can recommend the game, and I will be happy to play both in single player mode and in co-op. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": true}
