{"text": "It just so happened that Ancient Rome in the gaming industry is associated only with strategies for every taste. The reasons for this fact are quite surprising - in front of you is a whole collection of interesting stories that you don't even need to invent. But the developers are doing about the economy and politics on the global map ... And here Crytek enters the scene, wanting to release an action game in this era that will simply look amazing. And they did their job - the game, even after so much time, looks just great, which is quite expected from these developers. As well as the fact that the game will have other typical studio \"chips\". For example, Ryse Son of Rome is not particularly fun to play. A primitive combat system built on hit / bounce / block / roll can get bored with its monotony after an hour of play. Different scenery flashes, the plot develops, but we stubbornly run and endlessly chop enemies in the same way. And even finishing moves, which I liked so much at first, are beginning to enrage. And considering that most often you fight with opponents who look exactly the same, it starts to annoy. But, in some ways, Crytek has succeeded. It is, in fact, about the story itself. Yes, on the one hand, it looks as if the screenwriter was brought a handful of different pages from different books on Ancient Rome, so from the point of view of historicism everything is very sad here. On the other hand, why not? After all, the game immediately makes it clear that this is a kind of blockbuster game, where everything explodes beautifully and a lot of \"wow moments\". Well, what has Crytek been associated with for a long time is also here. The game looks incredibly beautiful. The landscapes are really mesmerizing as far as they are worked out. In general, Ryse: Son of Rome is not a must-buy, it is too focused on a certain category of players. If you need a strong combat, or you want to enjoy the gameplay itself - pass by. Well, if you love the entourage of Ancient Rome and are ready to close your eyes to historicity, then the game can please you with the opportunity to touch this era. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
