{"text": "Hello everyone. I would like to start my review with the fact that I started my acquaintance with the Gothic series with 3 parts and loved it very much and still consider it one of my favorite games! Unfortunately, I did not have a chance to play the first and second parts, so I treated this project with great interest and was glad to look at the modern rethinking and modernization of the first part. We do not undertake to consider optimization, lags, bugs in this mini-review as the project is still at such a stage when it\u2019s all forgivable, although by the way I have hardly encountered any bugs, and if there were, they were completely trivial and not serious. I would like to say a special thank you for the Russian localization for the teaser, after all, it is more pleasant to play and study a new game in your native language, honestly, I did not even expect that he would be there (Although later I remembered that the community of gothic fans from Russia was very large and the surprise went to second plan). As a result, in principle, this project looks good and overall I liked it, the old mechanics look good as well as the old look at the location design (it is clear that the developers did not want to modernize the game too much) Unfortunately, not everything is so perfect in this game, there is and a couple of points that need to be finalized about which I already wrote in the feedback to the developers, I hope they will listen. Namely: 1) The fattest and most serious problem in my opinion is a curve and not a convenient combat system. The crookedly copied combat system from For Honor is not the best choice that can only be made for this type of game like Gothic, in my opinion, the old combat system from previous games in the series would look more appropriate here, this same combat system is only disgusting, and even about the fact that when the number of opponents becomes more than two, then this combat system is not playable at all, I generally keep quiet! Hopefully closer to the release (if there is one at all), the combat will be changed (ideally), since this combat system for a budget project is far from the best option, or it is heavily modified. 2) Blind-eyed post-processing, colors and high brightness in the game. It was very uncomfortable to study the game world with such a visual, there are already solutions on the Internet to turn off certain functions and turn off post-processing altogether, but turning it off leads to a sharp decrease in brightness, so you have to turn it up almost to the maximum. In general, developers should take a very close look and make post-processing more usable, or at least more flexible. 3) Soundtrack. As a lover of music and soundtracks in games, I could not miss this moment, especially after such a masterpiece soundtrack from part 3. Here he is not at all, well, that's straight at all. I think that developers should also pay attention to this, provided that the budget allows it, since the soundtrack is also important, because it, in turn, very well enhances the atmosphere in the game, and in such games it is still very important. In principle, these are all my main complaints about this game, if you refine them, I think you will get a good rethinking of the first gothic. Let's look forward to the release <3 ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
