{"text": "Counter-Strike: Global Offensive (abbreviated as CS:GO) is an online tactical first-person shooter developed by Valve Corporation and Hidden Path Entertainment, who also maintained Counter-Strike: Source after its release. It is the fourth game in the main Counter-Strike franchise. GameMods:  -Classic Casual and Competitive: Counter-Strike\u200d\u200a'\u200bs most well-known game mode, both involving Bomb Scenario and Hostage Scenario missions. At the start of each round, players can purchase weapons and gear with money earned from various actions, from assisting on kills to completing objectives.   -Bomb Scenario: the Terrorists must plant a C4 explosive at one of two designated bombsites; the Counter-Terrorists must prevent the bomb from exploding, either ensuring that the terrorist team does not plant it or defusing it once it is activated. -Arms Race: a deathmatch-based mode where each player is rewarded for each kill with a new weapon, with the first player to get a kill with every weapon in a predetermined set winning the game.  -Demolition: a round-based mode that removes weapon and equipment purchasing, instead rewarding players who manage at least one kill by giving the next weapon in a predetermined set of weapons. After a second kill with that weapon the players are also rewarded a grenade (of a random type) along with their new weapon for the next round. -Deathmatch: a mode consisting of 10-minute matches. Players must gain the highest possible score by earning kills with different weapons or desired weapons. The number of points from a kill depend on the weapon. Players may also take advantage of bonus timers for different weapons, using them to score extra points. Like in Arms Race, players automatically respawn after getting killed, but also when they choose to respawn with bonus weapons. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
{"text": "While watching the scenery and taking pictures, I pushed the main line + branch line. After 40h+, I was still a little sad. At the end of a trip, I said goodbye with the old man. The open world game feels that this is the cruelest point: the human face does not know where to go, the peach blossom is still At the beginning, Xiao Chunfeng was just looking at the scenery, so I think it's worth it. The camera function also has filters, good! The promotional videos released by the Dedsec hacker team in the game are pretty good-looking. Some scenes in the game can only be entered when the task is done. When the task is over, you can't see it. The company's thoughts revisited the old place, and it turns out that the door is no longer interactive, and the BGM of different tasks will be different. Of course, Ubisoft\u2019s old problem: the task is slightly more repetitive, but some of the tasks are actually very creative, so overall I think that OK has some plots in the main line of the level design. For example, a member of DedSec, I won\u2019t mention it to avoid spoilers, it felt too sudden at the time. There is also a big boss, which gives me a feeling of being in control from start to finish. Why did the Finial mission suddenly kneel? I haven't played Watch Dogs 1, so when I saw someone, there was no fluctuation in my heart. The surprise of the blind production crew (not Aiden Pierce). . . . . . In addition! And the most important point! The same is the police, why are the police in San Francisco so active and imba? I drove for more than ten minutes for a certain car theft mission at the front end of the main line. . . New players should pay attention not to mess with the police, this is not the city of Los Santos next door. . . JOIN US!!! I played Watchdog 1 for the first time not long ago, and finally understand why many Dog 1 players don't like Dog 2. It is an indisputable fact that the characters of Dog 2 are not as plump as Dog 1 (Damian, Clara, Yordi, La