{"text": "Although the first game overthrew 10 years, the graphics still look good, I started the series with the second game. Considering the option to transfer the selections in the first game to the second game, you can start the series from the first game. A series connected with the Mass Effect 1-2-3 story. You can play by transferring your choices until the 3rd game. We play as Commander Shepard in the story of Mass Effect 2. As soon as we start the game, our ship is attacked and destroyed. Trying to save the crew, we are thrown into the void and die. An organization called Cerberus has been trying to find us and bring us back to life for 2 years. They finally manage to bring us back to life. After that, we start working with Cerberus to fight against other races that threaten the human race. While talking to someone in the game, you have more than one option and what you do affects the course of the story. That's why the choices you make are very important. We play the game as the commander of a 4-story ship. On board, we can talk to the crew, make armor and weapon upgrades, and go on missions. Even ship enhancements affect the story course. We go on missions with the galaxy system and extract the necessary elements from there to make improvements. As in the first game, I would like to thank the friends who released a Turkish patch in this game. We can play such a legendary series in Turkish thanks to them. If you do not want to deal with the door lock, hacking style puzzles that we encounter everywhere, I recommend you to install a mod. It can get annoying due to its being too much. You can find these and similar mods on nexusmod. Those who start from the second game without playing the first game like me can watch this video. The game is my advice to rpg lovers. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
