{"text": "\u201cIndie games are rubbish, which is not worth wasting your time on,\u201d An acquaintance of mine once said. I am very glad that I can refute such a statement. And, perhaps, This is the Police would be a good example. For me, this game became an excellent addition to the collection of excellent games, when I bought it, I was waiting for a police station \u201csimulator\u201d with an admixture of noir for a couple of hours. But in the end I got an incredibly deep and interesting game for 23 hours, but perhaps the gameplay here is not too complicated, from a word at all, but the game is not about gameplay, no matter how funny it may sound, but rather about the plot. The plot is really great here. The minor characters are well written, they are remembered, they have a personality, their own motives to act one way or another. It is interesting to watch this and, of course, make your own decisions, which will certainly affect the plot and the development of the situation in the city. This game is truly a real drama for Jack, the chief of police in Friborg, and you will certainly want to live it with him. As for the rest, the game also features beautiful jazz music, which will help you immerse yourself in this noir chaos of police work. So do not waste time thinking whether it is worth buying or not, it is definitely worth it! Time to become a part of a cruel story where everything is not without sin! ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
