{"text": "Dota 2's annual showdown of talented wizard duelists has regrettably come to a close, leaving us with a clear view of the now smouldering field. With some players having been in the scene for almost a decade losing out to others who weren't even old enough to use a computer when their opponents began as pros, the range of ages as well as expertise in Valve's multi-million dollar pro scene is remarkable. If you want to end up here one day, try mastering the best Dota heroes for beginners. But who sits at the top of the player pile, jostling for position and playing their hearts out for their chance at Valve's gigantic prize pools? With team rosters so volatile in the post-International period, some of these players may be looking to jump ship or get themselves an upgrade, whereas others have seen the successes of OG and Digital Chaos and may look to build from scratch like a Rocky training montage. Here are the best players in Dota to look out for in this year's roster madness. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
