{"text": "I really like The Crew series, but there is a lot to improve, especially on servers, where players from the same session disappear from your front and reappear after 1 minute. during races or while creating decorations, some occurring even in a very short time, a matter of seconds after returning from the previous disconnection. , compared to the first in the series, but the impression it gives is that some points in the graphic area regressed, such as shadows of monuments and some textures that should, after almost 4 years after the previous title, be better (even with graphics) in the ultra), not to mention buildings when viewed from afar that look like a 2005 game. The Crew 2 is \"heavy\" alongside other auto titles and doesn't run more than 60 FPS and something that bothers me a lot, . I really like the personalization and decoration system, adding shapes to form a perfect \"sticker\". They could have more color options for the wheels, like basic or matte, and not just colors like chrome. They launched it for R $ 200 (Gold Edition), with The Crew 1's \"Wild Run\" built in, which previously charged for the part, but without the PVP mode and factions, now we can create decorations, but without the custom event creation mode , I expected more car brands in this title, I expected more events, a stronger story and more content. But as they promised, we can only wait. I criticized, but I still recommend it, because I have fun with this game. Free Demolition Derby update launched, with PVP mode only for Street Racing, Hypercar and Demolition Derby, and a ranking system starting from Bronze 4 (in my view, still improving). ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
