{"text": "Alright I'm gonna have to change my review of this game, before when they released 2.2, it reworked the entire planetary system and changed it in a way that, at the time I saw as horrible and micromanagement hell. I, still think so, but I think it is for the better, it allowed for a much better and mod-able planetary system that isn't just playing tetris with buildings. As with nearly all the updates and DLC, Paradox really cares about this game. I think one big issue people have with this game, is that it keeps releasing DLC. Which is a valid issue, but you have to realize that the fact that DLC is still being released, means that Paradox cares enough to work on the game more and more. The argument that \"this game should have been released finished\" or that \"Paradox is just milking money from blind consumers\" seems asinine. If they simply released Stellaris and left it alone similar to other Paradox games, I have doubts that it would ever be as popular as it is now. The constant changes and updates keep making the game better. \"But what about mah moneyyy I dont like dlc bc it costs money.\" Oh shut up, the DLC is the only way Paradox can be supported as a game developer. Rather than just re-releasing the same game over and over again like some certain studios *ahem* EA *ahem*. People say that Paradox is worse than EA for the constant releasing of DLC, well I think the math otherwise checks out that even if Paradox releases constant DLCs, it still comes out cheaper than the yearly re-release of Fifa.  TL;DR Stellaris is a great game, please support Paradox by buying the DLC to support them and make the game better. Also don't hate on Paradox for releasing said DLC. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
