{"text": "The first unknown of all has been the choice of voices. It is famous that Spanish is very bad, I have tried it and although I find it exaggerated what is said if it is malillo, then in English but the fucker has errors in the pronunciation of her own names or she invents them. At the end I have put it in Polish, which seems strange to me especially when they speak a lot for a short sentence. Another point in which it is famous is having a very bad gameplay in the fighting system and I strongly disagree. The system is based on clicks with the mouse to attack but slowly, each click an attack and at the right moment another click to chain combos (which are unlocked if you acquire the ability when leveling up), with the right click you do magic (for now as a sling of force) that serves to move away and throw them to the ground. The directions if you give it twice in a row, it makes a quick movement to dodge (somersault, jump etc.) a priori is not a big deal, but when you are surrounded it goes well and you gain a few seconds to attack without being surrounded, apart from that it is cool. Although I admit that that great system with the hours is tarnished, the idea is good but it needs to be polished and it shows that it fails several times when you want to do some dodges. It also has three styles. A slow one for big men, a fast one for little ones and a group one in case they surround you. All this accompanied by a pretty good skill tree and a potion system that enhances skills. I would already like that for example the Nerver winter nights had this system to say one. Following another very famous point that is said, the spoilers with the books, contrary to what is read and heard, this game has important spoils of the game, those who are interested in books, read them first. To finish and not least, both the main plot and the secondary ones have a more than decent level and it knows how to maintain interest with a style reminiscent of the literary saga, especially to discard some secondary ones, these had that touch of independent stories that it has the first two books. Although it suffers from messenger missions but these sometimes can give interesting rewards. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
