{"text": "Absolutely incredible game bursting with charisma and personality, fast, robust and satisfying combat with interesting and likeable characters. This is honestly a better action game than DMC 4 and if DMC 5 didn't come out, the DMC brand as a whole imo wouldn't even compete with the likes of this. The set pieces, the combat, the characters, everything is literally taken up to 11 to a point that I found myself not having this much fun in a DMC game with the exception of 3. I can now see why DMC 4 turned out the way it did and I highly doubt if Hideki Kamiya made it, it would've been the same and this game clearly shows that.  Starting with the technical aspects which seem to be pretty damn good. It isn't RE2 remake or Gears 5 good but I can see that a lot of effort was still put in although I do have a few gripes. Firstly, G-Sync doesn't work even though this port was made fairly recently. Secondly, there is no Move list editor to make it so punching is square like DMC which I heard was unnecessarily not included in the original, so you'll have to go through the Steam Overlay to switch up buttons which is kind of naive for a release this recent that could've easily been included and lastly, ALL cut scenes, even the the in game ones, are 30FPS, even though it isn't that big of a deal, it could've easily been avoided for a release this recent.  Now that I'm done with that, I will now talk about the actual game which is just \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 amazing. With the exception of the poorly told story they shove in your face at the beginning, in a dialogue dump told while your expected to fight dozens of enemies and a particular boss that repeats himself several times over but besides that, I loved everything else about this game and I think this may be one of my favourite action games of all time. It just makes you wonder the kind of crazy $hit Platinum Games could come up with, if they were given the DMC green light, like Metal Gear Solid. Its also surprising how much I enjoyed this game because of the absolute garbage intro but was then quickly forgotten by some of the craziest set pieces and combat that I think I've seen in gaming. I'll now list just why this game blew me away like it did starting with: 1) The combat which is just spectacular. Enemies are actually aggressive and dodging at exactly the right time activating witch time fits fairly well with the combat. Very few games other than DMC have combat this refined and deep that just never gets old for me. 2) The Jeanne fight alone deserves its spot. 3) Very replayable due to the accessories and moves taking many many completions of the campaign to acquire them all. It also makes all your play through's vastly different due to all accessories being completely different from each other and only 2 actually being able to be equipped simultaneously and costumes costing a whole lot and having hefty and obscure requirements that can have you play this game 10 times and never get the same experience. Its replay-value I've never seen in a game in my life, much better than DMC 5's  imo 4) Vastly varied and unique character designs. 5) Ever-changing and dynamic situations that put you in interesting sequences. From being on a motorbike, to riding on a missile, I felt like the developers constantly strived for progression in this game to genuinely be different from whatever was before it and I commend the effort that was put in. Even though some people do hate the motorcycle sequence, I on the other hand appreciate it.   6) Mind blowing set pieces and cut scenes that I couldn't get enough of.  7) Ridiculous off the walls ending that just gets more insane as you go.  With all its positives and its surprisingly few negatives, I think it deserves a very high 9/10 which I truly think it deserves and is quite a rarity if you've seen my score list. If the story wasn't so poorly told at the beginning and quite hard to completely grasp to begin with, it could've just gotten away with a 9.5/10. I honestly think its that damn good and if you are a fan of the DMC franchise or action games in general and haven't picked this up, then its blind buy worthy if you have even a slither of a bit of interest in the game or the man who directed the first DMC and were he took his DMC influence and ideas. ", "voted_up": true, "early_access": false}
