{"text": "This is how you can briefly describe this game. The game really looks like the legendary FlatOut: Ultimate Carnage, but there are a lot of jambs. In appearance the rules and the first couple of hours - you get high and enjoy the game. But over time you see. If you read the whole review, in short: a nasty cheap fake with a bunch of technical problems. In multiplayer, I have not seen more than one player. The bots are quite arrogant. There is very little music and tracks themselves. There is no wheelbarrow balance. Ultimate Carnage> FlatOut 2 >>>>> FlatOut 4> Wreckfest >>>>> FlatOut 3 Didn't play in FlatOut 1. The number of arrows indicates the size of the gap between these games. The most important thing is that the game lags wildly, regardless of the power of the computer !!! I don't know what to call it correctly. Statters, lags, freezes, picture twitching, visual fps sagging, curved effects in the game - choose yourself. Vidos for clarity: My video. Confa: i5 6600, 1660Ti, 16 GB DDR4 Someone else's video, you can see it even better here. Confa: i7 4770k, 1080 ti, 24 GB Ignore the very low bitrate of vidos - it's YouTube that stung them. In the game, these lags are noticeably stronger than in the video. I have 60 fps since the vertical is turned on. If disabled, it will be 120+ fps. But it will be much more laggy, a full slide show. Conducted a survey among friends. For the overwhelming majority, everything is ok here. I tested it on two different monitors / computers: 60 and 75 hertz. Comrades with 144 and 240 hertz - also clearly saw numerous lags. Perhaps, they are not visible on some \"special\" monitors. On both vidos, strong lags are clearly visible in the first minute. If you see them, it means that you will ALWAYS also lag. The first hours will not be very stressful (probably), but then it will bomb specifically. I mean this: This is NOT a production. This is a common thing in every skating rink. The car seems to weigh nothing and takes off into space on any uneven surface. Often these irregularities are not even visible. Multiple turns on level ground are also guaranteed. Moreover, the opponents seem to be magnetized to the ground. They do not take off so much and often. And you are even turned around / thrown into the air after a normal landing from a springboard. If the first point about lags is doubtful and not everyone will see it. Then the problem with physics is clearly evident. It is highly discouraged to accelerate, crash into something, ride on jumps and rails. You fly at full speed with nitro at a standing enemy and ridiculous damage is inflicted on him. In another game it would be a frag at once, but not here. This is NOT FlatOut. In a normal game, there is the concept of \"country\" and this country is divided into several sections. Thus, in one race there will be one section, and in the second race there will be another section that is not similar to the first. Ie it will not be very monotonous. But in this game there is no such thing. There are only return routes. Because of this, it gets very boring because you understand that you were driving the same track literally 20 minutes ago. The tracks themselves are few. One track opens in general in the last cup in star (3rd class) cars. Better late than never huh? If in the first class on derby cars this moment was not very annoying, then already in the second - it was enraged. Moreover, if you started with the \"Flatout\" mode and opened new cars there, then you can immediately buy them for the career mode and ride them right away. No need for standard slow clamshells. Hence it follows - the whole class you will ride ONE and the same car on the same tracks. Fierce monotony i.e. In a normal game, there are two unwritten classes of wheelbarrows: heavy and fast. For example, on a heavy Canyon you won't be able to catch up with Jack Benton's fast yellow Sunray in an easy one. Here, too, they did not give a damn. The best car is the heaviest dump truck with the highest max speed in the game. It almost does not take off on uneven surfaces and drives the fastest. B-balance! In general, the whole career must be driven strictly on heavy cars. Expressways take is equal to suicide. The first bump and you flew into space. There is no one there, not one living soul at all. More than one lobby. When doing cartoon achievements with friends, I ran into a bug. This bug was not immediately apparent. Both friends came to me in the lobby by invitation and could not press more than one button, nothing answered, except for the task manager. Even the beloved Alt F4. Friends went not to one lobby, but to different ones. I had to go through an open search, since there is no one there, no problem. This is the only way to play together. Stunt mode (mini games where you have to throw out the driver). There are old mini-games, though complicated ones. There are also many new ones. Made with high quality. Only here you see the old Flatout. But due to the overestimated complexity, it was not easy here either. Especially in baseball. I sat there for over an hour to make gold. There is pure randomness. Obviously a failed game. You will catch a buzz only in the first hours. Further - one disappointment. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
