{"text": "Before going into the details which annoy, here is in a few lines the concept of \"Beyond Eyes\" which, if it had been well exploited, was rather well seen: Technically it is a walking simulator in the 3rd person in which you must help Rae, a little blind girl, to find her cat who has not come home. There is therefore no real interaction with the environment and history (if we can still speak of history ...) is written as you progress. The peculiarity of the game is that you do not have an overview. Like Rae, the landscape is revealed under your feet, like a blank page that gradually emerges. Only a few elements that put your hearing on the alert are perceptible in advance, a few colored scraps lost in the dazzling whiteness of the rest of the scenery still untouched by your exploration. The idea was however simple and beautiful. Even before starting to play and from the first lines of the introduction we understand that the story will be sewn with white thread: the story of a child who loses her sight because of rays of the sun .. At the moment I find the subject a little light, but why not? Let's give it a chance, and then I like children's stories. Perhaps this game could be recommended for the youngest? .. Well no, not even. The story, completely tasteless and dripping with sentimentality, does not serve the purpose. It's hollow and uninteresting. The creators, in need of inspiration, could have used the common thread (the cat) without necessarily trying to tell something, but no, they had to add more. The album \"Martine \u00e0 la plage\" seems to come straight out of a library in the nearby Pl\u00e9iade! Rest assured, there isn't much to read either. Just enough to fill you up in the evening when after 2 hours of walking you discover the end which is just sordid in view of the context. Please understand each other: I appreciate gloomy atmospheres, unexpected or sad endings, this is absolutely not a problem in itself! But there ... it's free, a bit like putting sugar on jam, there really was no need to add misery to misery. : \u26a0\ufe0f SPOIL \u26a0\ufe0f If the character of Rae is particularly slow to move, it remains coherent given the context. But why have she dressed up in a posture giving the impression that in addition to blindness she suffers from mental retardation or even psycho-affective disorders ?! Most of the time, she walks prostrate, bent over, head tilted forward and her arms folded as if her wrists had been tied. She is blind, poor little one, not retarded! Not content with having equipped it for the winter, we add a little phobia to it which, during the ride, quickly becomes particularly annoying: it is afraid of birds. If the slowness of the character is acceptable, the approximation of movements and the management of obstacles is not. The poor kid does not see the walls and the trees until the snitch is inside! As much to say to you that it eats of the pines. Of course, once \"in\" the obstacle and well .. one is in it: sometimes the character disappears completely, the image jumps in zoom, sometimes Rae is found again in the middle of a tree trunk .. it's more than approximate and really very painful because each time you have to get Rae out of his rut \u200b\u200bwith the clear feeling of having to maneuver a 38 tons! \ud83d\udcce In short, you want to discover a game of beauty halfway between watercolor and print? Forget \u201cBeyond Eyes\u201d for good and go look instead, who's sublime! ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
{"text": "\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 do I went full retarded? Pretty much no, but actually I really enjoy the game. Yes, I mean it, the game its is really fun! No \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, its considered the \"Second Worst Game on Steam\" and hated by almost all critics, which Im not really gonna super defend this game because I have to agree on some stuff. The looting in the game itself is actually pretty fun, scaling from huge varieties of weapons, food, armor protection, backpacks, and such. Zombies are not really that much of intense feel like other triple A title zombie games, so expect some stupid \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 to happen. (and bugs...). In terms of PvP and PvE is not really this game main thing, since it mostly feels like \"Shoot first, ask question later\", if you can bare the killing survivors or avoiding them (or purchase your own private server), then you might get through this alive. Since the game is also F2P (but is only trials and you can get that on their site), there also consist of  different type of servers, Public server ( Obviously... ), Trial Server ( for F2P people ), Private Server ( for privater looters or just average host ), Public Test Server ( Test-out for their update on current map or new map ), Stronghold Server ( No announcement on it ) and the Veteran Server ( for players that played it above it 100 Hours ). *Theres another one but its just complete crap. You have litterally 5 Characters creator ( 1 if you are on Trial ), even they die you can pretty much revive them or instant respawn ( with In-game GC). Not much you can really create as you just pick few of the pre-made ones. There is game credit such as regular cash where you can buy stuff from the market, theres GC, which you can pretty just exchange it for cash.... since the whole market uses cash... but what is other purpose of GC you ask? To revive your character and open up private server. Not much to really explain here.  Map itself is not really huge as DayZ but its actually a good scaling, meaning is so huge nor that empty, most of the building is enterable, so you can camp or find a spot to hide. Since DayZ is one time chance of survival and your loot could be gone at that time if you got killed, this game have \"Personel Locker\" (Moving Item placement) and \"Global Inventory\" (your personel item placement), so you can litterally collect and keep your items in it, making it a hassle free to go out and do anything. but it somehow falls really flat due to its huge amount fail on the developer team and support team, trust me, is not even pleasant. Got something missing or stuck? no \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 given. Accidently deleted your character? No one gives a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665. Need help on the games, NO. ONE. \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665. GIVES.  If you are a fan of Totalbiscuit, AngryJoe and other famous reviewers, seen some rant and such, it feels like this is a piece a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, but is not really that huge piece of \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, its playable and enjoyeble with your zombie killing friends and such. Would I recommend this game? Maybe. Should you buy this game over DayZ? Nah. It all depends on you, whether to play it or not. Score = 6/10 ( +Its a zombie mmorpg game, +Habit of looting, +The Feeling of the survival, +Crap tons of weapons, +Vault system to keep all the items you loot, +Fun playing people, -PVP community is abit abused, so be careful first-timer, -No PVE, -Marketplace is expensive, -Horrible support team, -Private servers are costly ) ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
