{"text": "This game is SO HARD. The story they focused so much on in this installment is a gruesome bizarre; The characters are 95% repulsive and retarded, straight out of a very bad Michael Bay movie. The level design also leaves a lot to be desired: what were once huge maps to explore for kill opportunities have become claustrophobic little \"challenge areas\", where if your desire was to reach the Silent Assassin ranking, they greatly limit creativity. (KNOCKEAR PEOPLE PENALTIES YOU WITH POINTS) What I should highlight is the gameplay in some aspects. Coverage mode is well implemented, even with the option to quickly advance from coverage to coverage with a single button. Instinct mode to camouflage a disguise that is not perfect in the eyes of more demanding NPCs. But the rest is deporable. Very idiotic AI with which you can play Tom and Jerry by brushing their backs. The Instinct mode that takes all the fun out of studying your surroundings by showing you the destinations of the guards and the ability to see through walls. The linearity of the missions that make you run through corridors abusing coverage. New features and beautiful graphics don't save the mess that is the rest of the game. I cannot recommend this game to any fan of the franchise or to a casual person. I recommend starting with Hitman 2016 World of Assassination or its sequel and discovering the rest of the installments such as Blood Money, Contracts and Silent Assassin. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
