{"text": "Takeaway Games. Issue 9. Need for Speed \u200b\u200b- another restart of the series. When the 2012 restart of Need for Speed: Most Wanted failed miserably, and the next cop chases in Need for Speed: Rivals came out for the second time in 3 years (the first time was in Need for Speed: Hot Pursuit), then the most greedy campaign in the gaming industry decided to return to the Undergroud formula. And in order to stimulate sales, it was decided to start everything from scratch and throw out the subheading. It is a pity that the Frostbyte engine was not thrown into the trash. Why are post-apocalyptic games not very popular online? Because constantly being in despair is annoying, and players quickly throw such worlds. Why don't they make games where the game is constantly happening at night? Because constantly being in the dark is also not comfortable and annoying. The action of this part of Need for Speed \u200b\u200btakes place constantly at night. And to strain even more, the game does not work without the Internet and can throw you out of the game if you lose your connection to the Internet. \u201cEven in a single player. You can't even pause. \" (c) Gufovsky. The second huge problem with the game is physics. In this arcade racing game, you cannot sit down and drive. You need to google how best to set up the car so that it is comfortable to drive. But why? There is Need for Speed: Payback, where cars are divided into classes and you can ride them comfortably out of the box. I am glad that developers are able to admit their mistakes. The third problem of the game is the live actors in the commercials. Firstly, they are complete nonsense, from which for some reason the player is ashamed. Secondly, they constantly call on the phone and are talking nonsense already there. Even Undercover did it better. Of course, the player has a silent camera, who follows these actors and is silent like a partisan. Compared to Payback, there is a smaller fleet of vehicles, but more opportunities to pump the power of cars. But are these capabilities needed when 5-6 parameters were enough before? And after pumping the car may go worse. Amazing. Graphically, the game does not cause rejection. But the constant night makes it difficult to examine the details. Plus the soundtrack is a jumble of unpleasant sounds. There are very few good tracks. In the same Payback, half of the songs were excellent, another 25% were not bad, and the rest were tolerable. In Need for Speed \u200b\u200bI only heard one normal track. Now I don't see any reason to buy this part at all, when there is Payback, where all the ideas that the developers planned are implemented much better. I think it's time for the Need for Speed \u200b\u200bseries to either do the remasters that everyone wants (Need for Speed: Most Wanted 2005) or move on and not use the same developments several times. I do not recommend wasting your time playing. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
