{"text": "Is your wallet ready for microtransaction? The cons overweighs this game, only buy it when on sale and that you are a SAO fan. I would have voted it Worst game I bought this year if it weren't because I am playing for the sake that my friends play it. I enabled comments so that you can flame me, I am not a fan of SAO -abyssmal weapon proficiency system that is tied to accuracy, unlocking new skills. Be prepared to grind to 1000 whereby on normal difficulty past 500, you will only get 0.1 proficiency gain randomly without abusing partner exploit to grind their same weapon type.  -same as above, lousy weapon balancing system. Dual wield is top tier because the stats boost from both sword add up. -bug causing character to be unrecruitable. -grindy crafting and loot system. Each set of equipment has min-max stat, though you don't need max stat to clear game but people are abusing craft for free exploits to get max stat. Else you will have to religiously farm raids or keep fighting divine beast for 1 try at it. Divine beast will only spawn if you kill a fixed set of enemies, which is extremely tedious.  -weird hitboxes and brainless boss AI. It is easy not to get hit, the bosses are slow, you could just stop comboing and walk away. Downside is that this will interrupt your risk (combo meter) which in turn affect your damage.  (Increased boss attacking tendency in 1.09 but lower resistance to ailment that is not a legit way to fix overly easy AI) -Easy anti-cheat affecting performance. Uninstalling it improves performance but you won't be able to play multiplayer.  -bugged quests. Personally short of a character Reona, some gallery entries that were tied to friendship quest, missing cooking recipe that disappears from the NPC after certain time. None of the other quests were designed missable, so those are classified bugged as they weren't intended to be missable. -brainless button mashing affection system -boring fishing system, press a button, wait 8 sec for system to display what you caught. Again with the RNG on equipment stats and low % of finding weapon/ accessory from fishing, it seem a major grind to reach level 20. -grindy partner AI system that requires you to constantly use your partner so that the game register your inputs in Art Codes. If you don't use them, you could download from a pool that is available online. They were uploaded by other players. Does it really have to be that complicated when you could have given the players full customization? Else you will need to constantly issue commands to them in order to get them moving. -raid boss is too easy, the RNG of equipment stats and getting the equipment you need out of a list is probably the only reason someone plays raid dungeon. You could clear it alone but it still requires easy anti-cheat enabled. -choices in dialogue that doesn't affect outcome. The game is text heavy, I skipped all dialogues from chapter 2 to 6 as it end up a chore to read. Voice over is in Japanese and it's partial. Prepare to do alot of reading -boring fetch quests, slay x amount of enemy, craft certain stuff. None is engaging, the reward is kind of bad other than the  reward for fishing rods which affect the % of your catches -level 50 cap. Predictably the rest of the content is in season pass, level 50 is rarely the cap in RPG. It is just a rough measure what portion of the game is unreleased in original content. Look at the price of the game and season pass, would that be justifiable? -other characters don't feel unique. Exception is Renly who is the only boomerang user in the game. -grindy incantation system. You equip incantation, break it, gain ascension points to exchange with a +1 form of random lists of incantation. +1 incantation has very low rate of breaking. Imagine 20% to break when taking enemy attack vs 4% to break. That's the difference. Why can't we unlock it and buy from shop? -sacred art damage/ EVD stats which accomplishes nothing. Sacred art damage is so low that you don't even bother with offensive sacred art. Poor stat balancing system and levelling. I am murdering bosses 120-130levels higher than me. (Update 1.09 lauch extreme raids whereby 2 of 4 raids cannot be cleared due to level cap)   And bad graphics: My Eugeo pass through walls, go under floor and can even walk in sky. Proof above. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
