{"text": "Artifex Mundi... your HOG/HOPA games used to be so much better. Okay, so, for the breakdown: The art was fine, fairly typical for these types of casual games. Nothing terrible, but nothing great. Voice acting ranged from  \"good\" - \"cringy\".  Story was far weaker than in many AM games - HOG/HOPAs never really have \"deep\" stories, but this one was weaker and more predictable than usual, with a very abrupt ending. Hidden Object scenes were fairly well done, with some odd or archaic names for some items (*pause game, go to Google to figure out what that word is* types...*), but still not too difficult, not too easy. Puzzles and minigames were far too easy, and had little to no challenge to them.  Felt like no effort had been put into making them require any grey cell activity on the part of the player. Honestly sad to see Artifex Mundi games declining in quality, especially those made by The House Of Fables.  The only thing this game has over a Big Fish HOG/HOPA is Achievements and (overpriced) Trading Cards. Casual games are fine, no-effort games ... not so much. If you must have all AM games... buy this one on deep discount. Honestly not worth the full price, not such a great buy for 70% off, like I paid. Really left a bad feeling, seeing how much quality and content Artifex Mundi games have lost over the years, especially in the last 2-3 years. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
