{"text": "Bad game, but with good game characteristics. Almost two thousand hours, in three years playing this. The time has come to rate this game. \"Dead by Daylight\" has already caught my attention, firstly, in having a very striking and well-produced soundtrack, the assassins' designers are spectacular, as well as their animations, which are convincing. The game, as everyone should know, is about 4 players against 1, this being the killer, henceforth killer, who must prevent the four survivors from escaping. This idea works very well and makes us try again and again to escape, even dying all day as a survivor. Hiding behind a tree and stopping to be discovered brings a great adrenaline and satisfaction that makes the game more incredible. The best of all is the upgrade system, improving the characters and assassins to play better and in new styles. I have tried several styles myself: stealth, poker, repairman, savior etc. However, the game lacks quality as a final presentation, not matching the total value of the game, even with so much content. First, because these contents are paid and expensive. Character customization DLCs are very expensive and some, exclusively, are purchased with real money. The game never got rid of constant glitch and bug problems. These are torments that always hinder the players' experience and progress. The balancing system is never perfect. At first, the game seemed much more balanced than it is today, even though the gears that instantly repaired the generators or hooks were destroyed forever. That's because the game was more dynamic and with multiple objectives for everyone to do something for the group to benefit, while the killer had to act more strategically, be very fast. Today, however; the survivors, even together, fail to have a balanced chance to escape. That's because it's so easy to be a killer. When I play as such, I kill everyone easily without any complex strategy, as the killers' perks have been improved over time, while those of the survivors have been lowered (take the perks: explosive run or decisive strike). To make matters worse, the killer can close the hatch giving no chance for the survivor to escape. The chance for everyone to win appears only when we encounter killers who are controlled by novice players. The goal is not for survivors to flee in all matches for sure. But when I, playing as a killer, manage to kill everyone, easily, in 20 consecutive matches, it is because there is something wrong. Thus, as it happens several times, when we realize that the game is already completely lost to the survivor, it is not uncommon to find players killing or disconnecting themselves, and even in the first minute of the game. At the beginning of the launch, it was very difficult to see these behaviors taking place. The Rank system is very strange, because now your rank does not improve for you to escape or for fulfilling objectives, but doing many diversified actions in a single game, deviating from helping the team to escape with the main objective: opening the gates . Before, one of the game's proposals was for you to decide to save one person or to act in a more self-centered way to save others. Currently, if you try to save others by repairing or distracting the killer, you are punished in the rank system. If you keep repairing the generator to open the gates, the game will discount you points for not saving someone in danger. This is cool, but there are common circumstances where dropping the generator and rescuing someone causes the mass death of everyone and the destroyed generators. Egocentric decisions were important in the game to decide the survivors' victory. Basically, three years have passed since I'm playing this. The game is one of the most fun to play with friends, but otherwise, it is frustrating due to the poor functionality of the systems of rank, programming, gameplay etc. The game never felt like it had left early access. On the other hand, it is an important game for new competitors to appear with better definitions, as well as the 'White Noise 2', which stands out for its quality and execution. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
