{"text": "Devil's Hunt is a third-person action game inspired by Pawe\u0142 Le\u015bniak's novel \"Equilibrium\", you play a character named Desmond in the game developed by Layopi Games. Even though Desmond is a member of a wealthy family with all the possibilities, things do not go as they wish and as a result of the developments Desmond makes a deal with demons and is sent back to earth to re-face the factors that made his life go wrong. The powers he gains will force him to choose between the light and the dark side. Although the story of the game is different at first, it cannot provide the same effect when the gameplay progresses in a linear structure. I can say that the story presentation is very weak and ordinary in the game that progresses in a linear structure. In the game, which takes an average of 5 hours, 2 hours are included as intermediate stage and affect the tempo of the game. The only thing that adds variety is that you can turn into a devil form and use it for a certain period of time when the rage mode is activated. Classically, you have a finishing move other than light attack, heavy attack and dodging from enemies and you see similar combat mechanics throughout the game. . Although Devil's Hunt is the first game of the developer team, it is a game that needs more work and is lacking in many aspects, it is not in good shape in terms of optimization except for linear game structure, poor story presentation, animation deficiencies. I would like to point out that it has a high price, such as 70 TL on the stage and the date I prepared the review, and it would be better to give it a chance when it fell at a more affordable price due to these factors. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
