{"text": "The premise behind this game is solid: high-octane action with awesome weapons you can use to blow the enemy to bits. What's not to like? Well, as it turns out, there's plenty not to like. What kills this game for me is the absolute \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 enemy placement and 'trap' mechanic that constantly punishes you for picking up items that are supposed to help you. Get ready to have charging Kamikazi AND missile lobbing enemies dropped right on top of you for daring to pick up a +1 Health item. Sure, it might have been my own fault for trying this game on the second-hardest difficulty, but I felt absolutely no shame in save-scumming the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 out of this title after the fifth time I was killed split seconds after picking up some desperately needed health packs. I don't mind difficult games, but I appreciate being given more than a split second to identify and counter threats, and strategic options. There is no way to deal with a game that constantly drops enemies directly in your face every time you make the slightest bit of progress except for save-scumming foresight. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
