{"text": "When I started playing many, many years ago (when it was still a browser-only game), the game was fresh and balanced (for the most part). Battle were fought with wit and hard work, and skillful play was heavily rewarded. After a few years, I decided to pick the game up for a few hours to see how it aged. Racist names, \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 hitboxes, ear rape in-game sounds...it was not enjoyable. Germans were completely invincible and had extremely overpowered guns. (A German SMG did way more damage than my upgraded sniper rifle per shot and was way more accurate), it's nearly impossible to shoot someone out of a vehicle even if your shot *should* connect. Squadron Supplies severely limit your play time per match since they don't count on anything. I went in to a lobby and just started whaling on the enemy team. Outplaying and outaiming them at every turn. Yet, when I swung back to help my team push a point...I was slaughtered due to running out of \"Squadron Supplies\" and a random enemy I had never seen nor was anywhere close to was awarded credit for the kill.  In addition, Germans were able to mass spawn tanks and completely outgun and outnumber my team's infantry. It was absolutely terrifying and we had no way to stop it. I wish the game would go back to how it used to be. Having to wait on your teammates to catch up so you can formulate a plan and carry it out, instead of running in and spraying your gun wildly. Now, sniping is next to useless. Some shmuck with a regular gun will snipe you from 500 meters and instantly kill you, even if you're covered in camo or behind a wall. TLDR: Devs \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 the game up, Germans are literal gods, people are generally toxic with their names, a German SMG does more raw damage than a sniper rifle and a tank combined. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
{"text": "I recommend this game. But for me there was a minus in the game that ruined everything that I liked about the game and this is that yubisoft decided to call the game assassins creed. Everything in the plot related to the lore of the assassins is terrible. This spoils the game and kills the desire to play it. After completing the quest line gates of atlantis, I decided that most likely I would not return to the game. Yubisoft, due to its greed, unwillingness to abandon the franchise, dealt a strong blow to a good game. Now you can go to the pros and cons of this game and the problem described above will not be taken into account. + Graphics_Playing on medium settings, I got only one pleasure from the views of Ancient Greece (but sometimes the textures go into soap) + Setting_Ancient Greece is implemented with a bang. Many great people of this time appear and everything looks authentic and atmospheric. + Role-playing system_It's not perfect, but very good. Actions really affect play and dialog choices too. The romance system is good, although there are not enough characters available. + Additional tasks_Of course, not all stages were successful in the game, but there are characters who give out interesting quests. And Socrates with his tasks and dialogues is simply gorgeous. -Farm_I spent 40 hours on the passage of the main quest. Considering that I took quests 2-3 levels higher, and to close such activities as: mercenaries, cultists, arena, at least level 47 is required. In my 67 hours I got only 49, of course, you can get this level before. But in any case, you have to spend enough time -Balance_Game is tailored for donation. If you buy a permanent boost exp, the level will always correspond to the level of the main quest. Or you have to farm, as I wrote about earlier. -Naval battles_Initially, the sea content seems interesting enough. The first boarding is very enthusiastic. But at some point it gets very boring. Why board when you can just sink the ship. Every naval battle is the same. And pumping the ship, the terrible grind of gold and resources discourages the desire to do all this. -Battle system_To fight you press blow, parry, dodge. Sometimes finishing moves occur, but they are also monotonous and occur quite rarely. But skills save the day a little. Due to them, the combat system at least somehow keeps interest in itself Based on everything that I wrote above, I can advise people to buy this game who they love the assassins creed series and its lore, or those who don't care about the world and the plot. If you are waiting for an interesting ancient Greek story, then at some point all your joy from the plot will be shattered by the desire of yubisoft to keep the franchise and shove the assassins where they don't need to. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
