{"text": "Gamehunt is not the worst platformer by the standards of steam's indie handicrafts, but it doesn't really stand out. There are 10 levels in the game, where you have to get into the skin of a jumping hare and bypass explosive hedgehogs, dynamite boxes equipped with a motion sensor, ubiquitous lava and some features of local lvl design, get to your rabbit. The game takes place in literally half an hour, during which we will visit, though not the most elaborate, but still various locations that will even have different soundtracks (!). There are questions about the order of the levels, because some of the later ones were noticeably lighter than those that were before. Sometimes it was quite painful to go through something, given the local area of \u200b\u200bdestruction from the explosion, but with the proper skill, they get away. There are only three lives in the game, which could be a big disadvantage, if not the save system, thanks to which I went through the whole game with the last one. But then I felt the very same technical problems: the game hangs if you start loading at the time of death. If you died, then you need to go to the menu and boot from there. And the downloads here are somehow indecently long! Even Borderlands levels load faster, mess! Considering that the game was made in a short time and costs the minimum price, it is still more good than bad. Simple, not very pretty, but quite diverse, somewhat possible. But alas, there are much brighter representatives of this genre and I see no compelling reason to spend time and money on this particular one. I wish the author success in future projects, but I cannot recommend this one. PS: And there seem to be non-working achievements here. I went through the whole game and did not give one ( ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
