{"text": "I really didn\u2019t expect that it\u2019s 2020 and there will be a click to switch scenes and promote character communication! There are only 2 scenes in total, and you can only click and move between the hangar and the combat command room; it is communication, but The character who operated by himself didn't say a word, just watched others say a few words and then disappeared. For such a big spaceship, you won't even draw a pie, and even your own character can't even see a small part of the body. The production team really saves money and effort. On this occasion, the screen will tear when you turn the screen, and even the subtitles have typos... You can choose to listen or not to listen to others, because it has no effect on the plot. The so-called other people are just a few more important NPCs. You mean the others? Sorry, those are all backgrounds. The first person in the whole journey, pilot the plane to start the mission, and complete the mission suddenly and go home. Get off the plane from the hangar -> go to the combat command room to listen to the instructions of the step -> set off again, a real tool man. A highlight of the game is that you can experience the story between the two camps, so you can customize two drivers. Character skins and actions can also be obtained by purchasing or completing challenges. There are also differences in rarity between them. Although they are meaningless, you can't see them after setting them anyway (laughs). To make up for the monotony of the game content, the production team used a lot of cutscenes to match the original music. Well, fans said they watched the movie on the spot. The operation feel of the fighter is average, but the operation interface is more realistic, and there are a lot of customizable options in the cab. According to the needs of the battle, it can be adjusted between speed, firepower, and shield. The shield can also choose to focus on the front/rear. Although the performance option of balancing is conservative, it also means that neither aspect is prominent. What I have to complain about is the low intelligence of the teammate's AI. They will perfectly copy every movement of yours while flying with you. I thought that my tool man was bad enough, but I didn't expect my teammates to only stand out. My \"Zhongxing Gongyue\" is really curious about where the production team has focused their energy. Choose your faction and start matching. 5V5, that\u2019s it? There is no star destroyer, no cruiser, and there are only 4 types of small fighters to choose from. There are only 6 maps, not only common with other modes, but also very narrow. If you are looking for a fierce space battle scene, you can only say a pity. There is no star destroyer or cruiser. You can only choose from 4 small fighters on each side. The only good point may be that you can change the configuration of the fighter according to your preferences. There are no obvious advantages and disadvantages between the different components of the fighter. The increase of one piece of data will inevitably reduce the other data, which will highlight a certain item of the fighter. Performance depends on how you choose. There are blood recovery points on the battlefield, which are shared by everyone on both sides, and need to wait for cooling after use. Similarly, some components and weapons of the fighter also have a cooling time, and collisions with obstacles or other fighters will also cause damage. After the fighter is destroyed, it waits to be reset and resurrected, usually only a few minutes in a round. The game does not require the Origin lander to start, and the multiplayer mode does not require an accelerator (personal experience). Priority of operation peripherals: remote sensing> handle> mouse and keyboard ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
