{"text": "I can't truly express how disappointed i am to see the sequel of one of the best first person stealth games of all times to be released in this state.  I made an exception with Dishonored 2 and pre-ordered it because Arkane Studios always delivered quality in the forms of excepcional gameplay, interesting plots and good optimization for PC. Now that is over. The gameplay might still be as exquisite as Dishonored 1, the artistic design as breathtaking and the plot as interesting. None of that matter when you can't play the game properly due to a few, but critical, technical problems.  Unfortunately some of them will never be fixed like the mouse sensitivity tied to your framerate, making your mouse aiming absolutely random at all times depending to where you are looking at. This one is real nightmare for me personally. Also, even if you disable mouse smoothing and friction, the mouse still feel unprecise and unresponsive due to some kind of hard-coded filter on it, that along with the FPS-mouse-tied problem i said above makes you feel more like drunk octogenarian grandpa than the most lethal assassin of the empire, destroying inmersion and any moments of joy this game could give you in the way.  The optimization on the other hand, is even worse (if that's possible). I'm running the game on a 970 OC, 2600k 4.4ghz, 16gb ram on Windows 10 Pro at 1080p. As soon as i got outdoors my framerate just wont go higher than 40FPS while looking at the open. No matter if i'm on Ultra, Very High or High, with filters or without them, the framerate varies maybe 5FPS, which is absurd to say the least. On Low i get over 50 and near 60 sometimes, but for some reason the game feels that it's playing at 30 FPS even if it's at 80. All this optimization problems are probably happening because of Denuvo's, Arkane having no clue how to optimize IdTech 5 engine, and being a console port designed for pad instead of mouse and keyboard. When you go to the controls tab in the options the first screen you get is to config your pad instead of your mouse. The mouse options are in the third tab. Priorities i guess. Mouse problems like this are very common in console ports with the sticks stuff really hard-coded in the game affecting the way the mouse should work, because it's usually emulating or dealing with stick filters instead of just being raw input.  Stay way from Corvo and Dunwall, for now. Let my broken heart and wallet teach you this lesson the easy way. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
{"text": "I went into this game thinking that it is better than Dota,but it was even worse ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": true}
{"text": "The gameplay itself resembles a typical roguelike - from the very beginning we are told about the random generation of dungeons, pumping; in fact, there is always a selection of several prepared options from which you can already become discouraged for the fifth race because of the same type of locations. The game has only 5 levels and 4 bosses in the story, all this is completed in three hours, no more. And that's only because of the stupid mechanics with obligatory allies who need to be recruited (basically, it's to choose the correct dialogue option for random) the first time. Otherwise? Start over! It is not entirely clear in general for what audience this was done, but the game at the end of the passage looks as primitive as possible. Usually, when a developer forces a replay, he has something to say and show. AWAY: Journey to the Unexpected, besides the cyclic passage of the same levels, the most simple enemies and a dull combat system, alas, there is nothing to show. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
{"text": "M yes. Just came in, and against me are already some kind of comers with laser cannons, ice beams and other nonsense. But despite this, I managed to smash everyone with my initial bucket. So the question arises, why do you need to buy something at all, if everyone can be smashed on the starting tank. In general, there is no balance by ranks, there is no point in pumping, and the shooting system is somehow not to be liked. 3/10 for transferring shit from the browser to the shit outside the browser, although in the browser it even seems more interesting to me. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": true}
{"text": "Don\u2019t catch too many plug-ins ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
{"text": "The worst part of the game is that it is very far between the 2 altars, so once you die, you have to start the whole map from the beginning and kill all the npc again, this can be so boring sometimes, you say damn it. The game is difficult but not fun, but in a very boring consistency. That's why I deleted the game. God help the receivables already. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
