{"text": "I followed andrew Gilmour's tweets for a long time in which he was putting our long teeth on us with the sprites he was preparing for this Slain, but once played, I must say that I did not like the result at all. Despite this, I have made the effort to complete it by collecting the pieces of the medallion (lest I miss something) but the process has been more of a torture than a fun. The whole problem comes because the game basically looks like a quick game made in flash. The gameplay is stiff and rough like splintered wood. The design of levels without any aspiration, bland and boring, With nothing more than to go through the scenarios from left to right, dodging crude traps, activating some lever and jumping on some platforms placed without any grace. The enemies are very bloody and well designed but they are beaten in a similar way without us being able to do much more to defeat them than the counter technique. And there is no more. After a reiteration of elements put to the tun-tun, the final boss arrives, which is usually somewhat more boring and tiring to overcome than the rest and to the next phase. That said, add that Andrew's graphic work is clouded by tons of high-resolution special effects flooding the screen to fill. Mix this, sprites with Hi-RES effects, which completely kills all the magic and compactness of retro-style graphics. So nothing, if you want to see perfectly animated bloody monsters and you don't mind getting bored like an oyster from start to finish, give it a try. If not, stay away because it only leads to boredom and frustration. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
