{"text": "If you ask me, is it worth buying the game? Honestly it is difficult to recommend this game, unfortunately I am a fan of the series since I had contact with Black Flag, it was a kind of love at first sight, so I started playing the oldest and the most current ones, and there was only AC Origins and Odyssey, so I recently decided to buy the two that appeared on sale, even on sale are Expensive games (Odyssey 91 the best version) and Origins (60 full too), for some it may not be a lot of money, but if you are collecting the savings for buying them, honestly, can drop out, it does not MAINTAINY compensate if you have an average pc. Esee game was probably produced to sell Ryzen processors (which are also at 100%) and new video cards, why doesn't it make sense, I have a GTX 1080 Ti with 16gb of RAM and i7 7700K which I consider a pc until High , but even with a machine that was supposed to run with surplus I'm having a huge performance problem, probably because of this m4ld1to DENUVO and VMProtect which is a lack of respect for consumers, they put several protections to avoid circumventing a MICROTRANSATION system in GAME HISTORY MODE, this is ridiculous, if they made a game with quality and did not fail, fans of the franchise would not think about pirating, piracy is a positive point in the market, many download to see if the pc can handle it, others played pirate and took the promotion for liking it and helping the developer, but unfortunately UBISOFT is a Total SHAME! Silly stories, more and more the franchise is losing its essence and this for me that I am a fan is extremely sad, AC Origins was not even very good, this one in history is disappointing. If you haven't played AC 3 yet and want to get the most expensive version of Odyssey you win two remastered games, in moral terms, it's just one more game for you to leave in the library and never open, UBISOFT is not ashamed in the face and really remastered a game, the bugs you find in AC 3 Original you find in remastered, graphics change almost nothing and the performance is grotesque. The AC problem started with AC Unity, which was one of the biggest shame ever seen in the industry. Making an open world game with reasonable graphics anyone can do. I'm not an analyst, but it was necessary, stuttering in games is the worst sadness there is, we invested a fortune in a computer to play at 30fps to see such a shame, from 60 fps to 40 and sometimes 30, imagine for those who have a weaker machine and believe in the requirements shown on steam, downloading 100gb is sad, now if you want to be angry with this game is to leave no FPS limit, the CPU consumption is ridiculous, forcing an i7 7700K to 100 %, which does not happen by limiting. I DO NOT RECOMMEND THAT GAME! A tip for those who got screwed and can't ask for a refund: Lock the FPS on the MSI which helps a little more to reduce stuttering. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
