{"text": "At first I wondered why this game had so many negative ratings. So I bought it at a discount for 10 euros to find out. I defeated the first two bosses. It was fun. Until I started fighting the third boss - the Confessor. That's when I found out that the important thing in this game is speed and dodge. My warrior moved as if he was swimming in tar. So I just decided to run around and hide in these chapels. But the figure gets tired as quickly as the asthmatic, and I couldn't even get away from his anchor. I struggled for 2 hours with this one boss. And this one boss changed my opinion. Throughout the game I felt that I was a bit slow, but it didn't really hurt the previous bosses. I slaughtered the first the first time and the second the third. It was fun, I even wanted to give a positive review, but unfortunately I can't, because: the character is too slow (a warrior anyway), the camera work is difficult, I often couldn't hit the opponent, the hero's hitbox is definitely too large, and the range of his weapons is too large little. Bosses aren't that strong after all. It's just that the game is made in such a way that it is hard to play. I happened to get stuck between invisible walls, or just get stuck in an opponent. Besides, the story isn't very interesting either. Lords of the Fallen is simply a copy of Dark Souls. And it's worse. Unfortunately, I cannot recommend this game to anyone, unless someone likes to be nervous and likes the game to be difficult only because of their mistakes. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
