{"text": "Not recommended, sadly I have to admit, it's not what I thought it was. The game has really incredible and well-finished graphics, the commands are not bad (there is the fact of creating combos with the available moves), perhaps a little uncomfortable but very varied with many moves available. After finishing the tutorial you enter the actual game, to its own features, which I can confirm very disappointing, despite the various modes: BR, deathmatch, team deathmatch, and other mods (up to 64 players) standard of each game, you can not find the desire in any ... Mainly the game does not work, unbalanced due to the players and their way of playing as it is mainly based on luck and the skills you have. The reason? The players lash out at you en masse so as to have the kill confirmed and then move on to a next target, it is not a real pvp, but a mass rape ... The worst is being in front of players who lagging or spamming the main attack, difficult to manage but easy to ruin the game, not to mention that the ping (rarely) increases totally randomly, although the connection continues to work in the same way, without mentioning the game search menu, putting the timer on you would probably be able to spend 5 minutes good and good. Despite these problems and an endless wait I decided to try most of the modes in sigleplayer with bots, and guess what? I was hoping it was interesting and it could entertain but I was wrong, auto aim bots are quite difficult to take down, think when you get a dozen (this happens even when you set a few bots in the game), you die and then respawn and start over again the delirium. I was expecting a game similar to Stronghold, a new and different type of Stronghold as the buildings, troops, weapons and constructions are the same, or at least they really resemble each other but the gameplay strongly deviates from what is expected. really play. In the end, if I should do a summary of Mordhau I would simply say ... * Medieval Battlefield 1 *