{"text": "I don't know how such a game could be made. I really don't know. Did you think Fallout 3 was the pinnacle of the bottom? No, you are wrong. What is Fallout 4? I'll start with the most annoying things. From the very release, the game did not have adequate difficulty settings, and the \"survival\" that was originally sewn in is generally complete hell. You had to plant 20 bullets in the head of an enemy with a lead pipe, which kills you in two hits. Maybe I'm exaggerating, but after seeing the mission to save Valentine, I generally wanted to throw the PC out of the window and go crying, covered with a blanket, there was such a balance and interest from the gameplay. I'm a pretty good player, but since I was more involved in roleplaying and always lugging something to my bases in the wasteland, from time to time improving them, I really did not improve any of the weapons, and due to reluctance to spend caps I almost did not use consumables like grenades. I think that if you do not initially pump all the points into the combat perks and set your brains on fire with thoughts of how to upgrade which weapon and how many grenades to stock up, then such missions in the middle stage of the game will never be completed. Okay, all this was before, but now, for sure, everything has become better and the nonsense is fixed, a person who has not played the game might think. No matter how it is. An update for the survival mode is coming out, which our Todd Howard is still very enthusiastic about, but what do we get with this update? The first few lines of description are even pleasing to the eye: the character's thirst, hunger, the need for sleep, changes in the carried weight, a new feature \"adrenaline\", a realistic combat system (1-2 shots to the head and you are already a corpse, the same with the enemies) ... But what goes on next ... Just think about the essence of what has been written: all the saves have been REMOVED, now you can only save by sleeping in bed, cut out a fast travel (you should have seen the size of this world, damn it, if you collect all kinds of rubbish and stagger back and forth , and not run through the story company). And hunger and thirst behave absolutely inadequately. Perhaps someone will like the lack of saves, it still adds hardcore to the game, but in a post-apocalypse game, I would like to have an atmosphere due to the complexity and the ability to die for any little thing. Yes, they will clearly allow you to customize this mode to your liking, they will not force all players to play with such a specific gameplay if the player selectively wants to get something from the mode. ... Do you really believe that? Yes, they thought of leaving such an unbalanced mode without any possibility of adjusting it. Plus, they \"banned\" the console in it, and the \"tfc\" command, which helps to set up the camera as needed and take a screenshot, as far as I know, was completely removed from the game with the release of the update. In addition to all this, I, like other players, want to note that the paucity of dialogue is very upsetting. Quests do not shine with an interesting plot either. The main plot twist can be predicted by many almost at the very beginning. Character customization is not done very well, although it is not really needed here, so let's not quibble. The armor of the BS and the Enclave, as for me, was drained here, what kind of batteries from the flashlight are there, that they are discharged in minutes for three runs in it? There are some disadvantages that will be individual for different people. But despite all this, I can say that the game easily finds its audience and has many interesting ideas and gameplay features. To play it ... but you can't play it in any way, they didn't bring in adequate settings for a person. I generally cannot tolerate this broken feature with survival, and without elements from this very survival, the game does not feel the way it should, and I also want to choose the balance for the battle myself, so it's not comme il faut. Since I cannot play the product at all at the moment, and I think other people may have the same reaction to such ideas of the Gazebo, I cannot recommend it. I will follow the updates, and if one day the patch \"fixes\" the game, then I will go through it, and it is quite possible that even more than once. By the way, I'm not the only one who dislikes this survival and wants something like in Vegas, on the Internet I came across more than one topic describing the same problem. To take or not to take the game now is up to you. If you still read my angry review to the end, then the review is welcomed, positive or negative. Thanks for attention. P.S. There are a couple of inaccuracies in the review, which were then corrected in the comments. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
