{"text": "The main part of the plot of this novel is the story of the girl Mirai, her romantic feelings for the main character, with a \"type\" unexpected twist at the end of the game. But it didn't work out as I wanted. As a character, Miray appears in the game spontaneously from time to time, sometimes out of place with his mysticism and the desire of the reader, it annoyed me. In addition to the final chapter, devoted entirely to Miray, the script mainly told about the protagonist and his friends, it was they who worried me more than the future girl of the hero. In general, the motivation of the hero to run after her and do stupid acts is not clear. Notes: * No change in relationship with her sister Rin is shown. * Lillian and Lucas. One of the most interesting things in the novel that interested me, a rather long intriguing moment, is the romantic conflict between the protagonist, his friend Lucas and mutual friend Lillian. Which ended in nothing. There was no plot denouement of this intrigue, no consequences. And the dramatic notes are quickly washed away by the snotty final chapter and the final stupid happy end. * Drawing in some places sags a lot. * Soundtrack is weak. In general, in this novel, the choice of the hero does not affect anything absolutely. Some choices only lead to more interesting dialogues, and in some places even to scenario inconsistencies. For example, a scene with a window, when choosing the first option, when the hero runs away from home, the sister does not react to this in any way and somehow gets to know Miray. This is a scripting error. The presence of elections is pointless, the plot is completely linear. The author of the game just wanted to show a romantic story, it turned out not original and in places stupid. There is a lot of excess water in the plot of the novel, and it does not end with anything like that. I didn't see what I wanted to see in the game. Although, maybe, as for a small free project, it's pretty good. But the s