{"text": "This review contains only the opinion of the author regarding this game product, which may not coincide with yours. I'll start with a little prelude. Each of us, when getting acquainted with this or that game, expects to get pleasure from it in one way or another, which both justifies the price that the creators of their creation ask for, and the time given to it. Game developers use a variety of ways to achieve the goals of the player. The main ones are either through \"gameplay\" - the creation of special game mechanics, in which the player, in case of success, experiences a feeling of happiness from the result of his actions, or through the plot - the player's immersion in this or that story, which is covered by the general message of the creator, the so-called idea. Eliza is not difficult to guess trying to \"satisfy\" us through the plot, but did she really manage to do it? Now let's figure it out. Before delving into the details of the plot, I suggest that you familiarize yourself with some of the gameplay elements. The game provides for certain moments where the player must independently choose one or another solution. So there are 2 types of choice. The first of these influences further history; this or that ending will depend on it. The second one affects the so-called \"karma\" of the character and the response of this or that character after this choice. What is Karma? Karma is simply an icon of a character in the codex - a short description of the character's history. These karma points do not affect the subsequent behavior of the hero, and even more so the ending, these are simple pretty images of the main characters, but nothing more significant. This karma scale has not brought any innovations to the genre of visual novels. Visual design of the novel. It is worth to pay tribute to some of the arts in the game are really very soundly visualized, although the depicted on them in some cases does not quite correspond to what is described in the story, but this does not detract from their beauty. Some of them can be classified as extremely wobbly. In general, the visual component can be approved. The artists were certainly not too lazy. Plot. In it, the creators have done the most blunders. One way or another, the whole action revolves around Lizanka, the hostess of the tavern. In fact, the game tells 2 stories. Exit to one or the other depends on the choice at the beginning of the game. And the main problem lies in the fact that the characters are not sustained. In the first thread, she appears to us as a freedom-loving girl with the makings of a manipulator in relation to each character, whose image I was extremely impressed with. Everything is subject to her own interests. She knows what she wants to achieve from people and through certain tricks, especially in relation to men, she always achieves the result she needs, even if they try to resist her will. In the second branch, she appears as an ordinary melancholic simpleton who forgot about her freedom and, without hesitation, exchanged it for love, which is not typical for Eliza from another branch, who for some time thought that it was more profitable for her. Unfortunately, the positive impression of what is happening in the game is violated by the moments when the igruha herself neglects and forgets both the laws of common sense (the moment with the knight who reads the book, apparently hoping to find peace in the tavern dining room - this is probably a quieter place than his own number), and about those laws of the game world, which she herself puts before the player (Eliza reveals the lies of two actresses who are supposedly noblewomen, guided by the fact that noble girls travel only with their accompanying guards. In another branch to the tavern a real wealthy noblewoman Francesca, who for some reason also traveled unaccompanied, is already coming to Eliza). The main disadvantage is the lack of any artistic value of this product. In fact, this is