{"text": "Almost 5 months development time for the new DLC from Planet Zoo. That certainly means that the developers have taken the many negative reviews of the last \"enhancements\" to heart and are now improving the content? The reality looks different, more development time for consistently low content. 5 animals which were partly recycled from known animations and changes in textures, such as the cassowary / ostrich and the dingo / wilddog. I think the koala and the kangaroo are beautiful, but not enough. The terrarium animal is very nice. Why not invest a little more time for the emu, which also differs little from the cassowary? The components as always, some of them quite nice, but not even remotely worth the money. After the unsuccessful attempts to create an extensive Arctic and South America pack, the potential of an Australia pack has now been skillfully given away in the usual tradition! A future European pack with 5 animals (lynx, \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, wild boar, and fallow deer + the terrarium with a frog, for example) would almost be a stroke of genius ... Here too, countless animals would miss their entry into the game, because the European animal world is very diverse. Brown bear, martens, badger, red deer, roe deer, squirrel, beaver, elk, raccoon, goat, sheep, hare, mouflon, pot-bellied pig, ibex, donkey, chamois, marmot, pond turtle, gray wolf (already included in the main game) and much more. A similarly diverse array of animals could be put into a terrarium. Toad, horned viper, adder, slow worm, forest lizard, garden snail, salamander, hedgehog, field mouse, aspic viper and much more. I will not go into the water and bird species at all, as this has still not found its way into PZ. How many bites have to be waited and bought for the total scope of a zoo tycoon at that time ??? I think most of them have forgotten that an expansion package at Zoo-Tycoon2 consisted of between 20 and 25 new animals, new game mechanics such as stage shows, water shows, etc. Now there are gamers again who defend this by saying that the graphics were also much weaker. You have to know that there are completely different technologies and techniques in development today! Expected more from Maxis - sorry Frontier. In this example I have to say that Maxis usually offers more to customers. On sale for 4.00 - 4.50 euros OK. I have to keep saying that I am willing to pay more, but I would also like to see that the developer makes an effort. I find it frightening that there are astonishingly many people who think the approach is great and celebrate it, the expectations of today's players are obviously sinking into the abyss ??? Saying the developers listen to their community is only correct to a very limited extent. PS: The path system is still really bad. Raised paths always form curbs and ugly crossings. With the setting Flatten terrain, the terrain around the path is also changed, why not only directly under the paths? The paths cannot be connected completely freely either, but block each other. Unfortunately, this is one of the biggest problems, and it is almost 100% certain that it will never be fixed, as Frontier is obviously unable to do so. Hope there will soon be competition from other developers in the field of zoo simulation. Update 08/28/2020 I read a review that says that the price is justified because all the many employees have to be paid. I'm ready to pay more as soon as I get the impression that the many employees are actually working intensively. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
