{"text": "In all honesty this game has disappointed me. For me personally Saints Row is a game of over the top ridiculous nonsense (at least in recent additions to the series) and this game is just not there.  Gat out of hell's plot is weak. The game feels like for of a Dlc such as how the saints saved Christmas in IV or Trouble with clones in the 3rd. I'll give you a list of the things I've liked and not Pro's \u2022 Good upgrades on abilities  \u2022 You get to play as Johnny Gat (!!!) \u2022 See some old characters from the series \u2022 The weapons you get are pretty awesome (though not a patch on the dubstep gun from IV) Con's \u2022 Annoying characters!!! (Can't stand the devils daughter) \u2022 Lack of character from the main crew - you only see characters such as Pierce and Shaundi at the start and end) \u2022 All the side quests are annoying or boring - there wasn't a single one I liked \u2022 The wings are hard to control \u2022 The map is quite boring \u2022 THE VEHICLES - can't save any and they all look awful \u2022 No music - like cmon really? \u2022 The game is so short - like who is going to get the 40hours+ achievement when the campaign takes 8 hours to complete  I love the saints row series! But this game just doesn't fit with the general theme. Hope it doesn't look like I'm complaining but is my honest opinion of the game. Disappointed as this game was the most expensive one I bought in the series and it was the worst (imo) ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
{"text": "I had this game on my steam wishlist to watch for it to drop below pocket money on a sale, and someone bought it for me at full price. I wish I could get them their money back. I am of the opinion that in a game like this, any player should be able to jump into any class, derp around with 1/8th of one clue and still demolish the first level to such a degree as to be made to feel like a complete champ, and by so doing, be sucked into the game. Heroes of Hammerwatch fails that bar spectacularly. No guidance is given, death is swift, permanent and run-wrecking, and traps which are set up to seem like fairly mundane timing puzzles will slaughter you instantly; if they are in fact timing puzzles, then even the Ranger, whom would presume to be the swiftest of the starting classes, is insufficiently fast to make them. I figured the first time was mistake on my part, but the second one, I am sure was not. I'll keep grinding my head against this bomb for a bit to see if it can overcome the poor first impression, but my expectations started out middling, foundered when I realized that character customization extended only as far as recoloring your beefdude instead of choosing to play as a female character, and are currently sinking fast. [edit] After some time playing this game with the friend who got it for me, I have concluded that, while all of the above is applicable to single-player, multiplayer more than saves it. This is not a great game to play alone; this is a great game to play with friends. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
