{"text": "It pains me to give this game a negative review because Call of Duty 4: Modern Warfare is not just one of my all-time favorite Call of Duty games but also one of my all-time favorite Military shooters. But the PC port for this   is just a pathetic excuse. And this is a real shame because this isn't just one of your typical remasters. I can easily classify this as a full-on remake. The graphics, textures, lighting are so good and pleasing, the weapon sounds are extremely high quality and pleasing to the ears, the immersion is top-notch and the small little details add on top of this makes this game worthy of the title of a Remake. But the PC port is perhaps one of the worst I have ever experienced forcing me to give it a negative review. It is 2011. A civil war has broken out in Russia between the current government and an Ultranationalist faction who are wishing to restore modern-day Russia to the Soviet-era glamor. Meanwhile, in the Middle East, a separatist group led by Khaled Al-Asad overthrow the government of an unnamed Middle Eastern country through a Coup d'\u00e9tat promoting the US to lead an intervention to avoid the destabilization of the region even further. In the meantime, a new recruit by the name of John   MacTavish is undergoing his final recruitment training in the S.A.S   before joining Bravo Team on a mission to the Bering Strait. Just another day in the field from the looks of it... \u25cf Engaging story \u25cf Well written and likable characters \u25cf Diverse and unique levels \u25cf Big weapon pool \u25cf  \u25cf Steam Achievements \u25cf Collectibles \u25cf Beautiful graphics  \u25cf Immersion  \u25cf Performance  \u25cf Crashes galore  \u25cf Dead multiplayer  \u25cf Activision's Greed  \u25cf No FOV slider  \u25cf No Steam trading cards  What could have been a glorious remake of a fantastic Military shooter has turned into a nightmare of crashes and greed. Unless you're planning on purchasing IW then I highly advise you to steer clear from this donkey sh*t of a PC port. If you're looking to replay the COD4 campaign out of memory or nostalgia then do yourself a favor and just buy the original COD4 on Steam or go and buy MWR on the console. Only buy MWR if you're an achievement hunter and wish to collect all of the achievements. The original COD4 doesn't have achievements which is what prompted me to buy the remake in the first place. Whatever your decision for purchasing MWR will be in the end, do know this. You will be fighting the crashes and time to crash a whole lot more than you will be fighting the Insurgents or Ultranationalists. ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
