{"text": "Completed the third part of Tomb Raider. I am disappointed with her. Alas! Achtung, spoilers possible! :-) I'll start with the good. As in the first and second parts, I liked the landscapes, visuals, locations. Normal gameplay, interesting stealth, various challenges, more side missions, a large arsenal, normal crafting of equipment and weapons. Good, celestial characters. The rest left a bad aftertaste. Here's the plot. Weak, boring, no intrigue. Interesting moments are off-screen, like the hunt for Trinity. Misunderstandings about Lara's dad. In part 2, we were convinced that he was out of his skin, quarreled with everyone, wanted to find Kitezh, and here they already declare that he did the same thing to find Paititi. And in the end he was slammed not for Kitezh, but for Paititi. The feeling that the writers could not be determined. Her, maybe I didn't understand what the plot was, well, you too, as storytellers, could try. The gameplay has been reduced mostly to puzzles in tombs and crypts. This is an interesting feature of the entire series, became the will of the developers directly dominant. The first 20 hours I liked everything, but then I began to tire. Yes, and there is a loss of dynamics in the narrative because of them. I also didn't like the chosen culture. This is of course subjective, but I liked the Japanese style from the game of 2013 and the Slavic-Byzantine from the 2nd part much more. Well, somehow I do not have a soul for the Incas, Mayans, Aztecs. Also a bit bored. Even during the game, I could feel the developers' laziness, or something. There are a lot of repetitive elements per square meter :-) Here I am doing a task, as a result, an NPC dies in the cutscene, next to him is his relative, well, one to one dying :-) And then a new task gives the same model, only with a new hairstyle. Even with collectibles were lazy, a huge part of them are copies of each other. I honestly don't remember this in the previous parts. Each item was unique, I looked at them with pleasure, twisted them, twisted them, read their history. But this was not the case, they dropped to the point that there were 4 completely identical things. Nahua you added them ??? Unpleasantly surprised by the bugs with the light. At the junctions of locations, there is always a total illumination. It's like lighting from multiple locations is superimposed on each other. You stand still, turned the camera to the left, a supernova flash, turned the impenetrable darkness to the right. In some areas it is impossible to be, you have to cut the brightness. I'm tired of criticizing the game, remembering its jambs, especially I didn't write them down :-) In general, I really liked the first two parts. And I think that against their background 3, the game is much weaker, as if the developers are tired of doing this project. Even in the ending, there is no hint of new adventures. In general, the game is normal, but I personally, for my subjective taste, did not like it. Hence the thumbs down. But in principle, you can buy, especially if you have the first two parts in the collection! P.S. Larka bust, top !!! :-) ", "voted_up": false, "early_access": false}
